const resolveMockPreset = useCallback(\n    () => getSimulationMock(SIMULATION_MOCK_PRESET),\n    []\n  );\n\n  const pushMockTimelineEvent = (partialEvent) => {\n    setTimelineEvents((previous) => [\n      {\n        id: partialEvent.id || `mock-event-${Date.now()}`,\n        timestamp: partialEvent.timestamp || new Date().toISOString(),\n        ...partialEvent,\n      },\n      ...previous,\n    ]);\n  };\n\n  const hydrateMockSetup = useCallback(() => {\n    if (!isMockSessionEnabled) {\n      return;\n    }\n\n    const preset = resolveMockPreset();\n    if (!preset) {\n      return;\n    }\n\n    const { setup, gameState: presetGameState } = preset;\n\n    if (setup) {\n      setPersonalities(setup.personalities || []);\n      setSuggestedOpponents(setup.opponents || []);\n      setCourses(setup.courses || {});\n\n      if (Array.isArray(setup.opponents) && setup.opponents.length > 0) {\n        setComputerPlayers(\n          setup.opponents.slice(0, 3).map((opponent, index) => ({\n            id: opponent.id || `mock-opponent-${index + 1}`,\n            name: opponent.name,\n            handicap: opponent.handicap,\n            personality: opponent.personality,\n            is_human: false,\n          }))\n        );\n      }\n    }\n\n    if (presetGameState?.players) {\n      const humanPlayerFromPreset = presetGameState.players.find(\n        (player) => player?.is_human || player?.id === \"human\"\n      );\n\n      if (humanPlayerFromPreset) {\n        setHumanPlayer((prev) => ({\n          ...prev,\n          ...humanPlayerFromPreset,\n        }));\n      }\n    }\n  }, [isMockSessionEnabled, resolveMockPreset, setPersonalities, setSuggestedOpponents, setCourses, setComputerPlayers, setHumanPlayer]);\n\n  const runMockSimulation = () => {\n    const preset = resolveMockPreset();\n    if (!preset) {\n      return;\n    }\n\n    setGameState(preset.gameState);\n    startGame(preset.gameState);\n    setShotState(preset.shotState || null);\n    setShotProbabilities(preset.shotProbabilities || null);\n    setHasNextShot(\n      preset.hasNextShot !== undefined ? Boolean(preset.hasNextShot) : true\n    );\n    setInteractionNeeded(preset.interactionNeeded || null);\n\n    clearFeedback();\n    (preset.feedback || []).forEach((entry) => addFeedback(entry));\n\n    setTimelineEvents(preset.timelineEvents || []);\n    setPokerState(preset.pokerState || {});\n    setBettingOptions(preset.bettingOptions || []);\n    setMockStep(0);\n  };\n\n  const handleMockDecision = (decision) => {\n    if (!isMockSessionEnabled) {\n      return;\n    }\n\n    if (decision.offer_double !== undefined) {\n      handleBettingAction(\n        decision.offer_double ? 'offer_double' : 'decline_double',\n        {\n          label: decision.offer_double ? 'Offer Double' : 'Decline Double',\n        }\n      );\n      setInteractionNeeded(null);\n      setPendingDecision({});\n      return;\n    }\n\n    if (decision.accept_double !== undefined) {\n      handleBettingAction(\n        decision.accept_double ? 'accept_double' : 'decline_double',\n        {\n          label: decision.accept_double ? 'Accept Double' : 'Decline Double',\n        }\n      );\n      setInteractionNeeded(null);\n      setPendingDecision({});\n      return;\n    }\n\n    if (decision.accept_partnership !== undefined) {\n      const accepted = Boolean(decision.accept_partnership);\n      pushMockTimelineEvent({\n        type: accepted ? 'partnership' : 'solo',\n        description: accepted\n          ? 'Mock: Partnership accepted. Robots brace for teamwork.'\n          : 'Mock: Partnership declined. Captain must go solo.',\n      });\n      addFeedback(\n        accepted\n          ? '‚úÖ Mock confirmation: partnership locked in.'\n          : '‚ö†Ô∏è Mock decline: prepare for solo play.'\n      );\n\n      if (!accepted) {\n        handleBettingAction('offer_double', { label: 'Forced Solo Double' });\n      }\n\n      setInteractionNeeded(null);\n      setPendingDecision({});\n      return;\n    }\n\n    if (decision.action === 'request_partner') {\n      const partnerId = decision.requested_partner;\n      const partnerName =\n        gameState?.players?.find((player) => player.id === partnerId)?.name || partnerId || 'selected partner';\n\n      pushMockTimelineEvent({\n        type: 'partnership',\n        description: `Mock: You selected ${partnerName} as your partner.`,\n      });\n\n      addFeedback(`ü§ù Mock partner secured: ${partnerName}`);\n\n      const pressurePreset = getSimulationMock('pressureDouble');\n      setInteractionNeeded(pressurePreset.interactionNeeded || null);\n      setShotState(pressurePreset.shotState || shotState);\n      setShotProbabilities(pressurePreset.shotProbabilities || shotProbabilities);\n      setBettingOptions(pressurePreset.bettingOptions || bettingOptions);\n      setPokerState((previous) => ({\n        ...previous,\n        ...pressurePreset.pokerState,\n      }));\n      setMockStep((previous) => previous + 1);\n      setPendingDecision({});\n      return;\n    }\n\n    if (decision.action === 'go_solo') {\n      pushMockTimelineEvent({\n        type: 'solo',\n        description: 'Mock: Captain elects to go solo and press the wager.',\n      });\n      addFeedback('üöÄ Mock solo play engaged. The wager has been doubled.');\n      handleBettingAction('offer_double', { label: 'Mock Solo Double' });\n      setInteractionNeeded(null);\n      setPendingDecision({});\n      return;\n    }\n\n    if (decision.action === 'keep_watching') {\n      pushMockTimelineEvent({\n        type: 'captain',\n        description: 'Mock: Captain keeps observing robot tee shots.',\n      });\n      addFeedback('üëÄ Mock mode: continuing to observe tee shots.');\n      setInteractionNeeded(null);\n      setPendingDecision({});\n      return;\n    }\n\n    pushMockTimelineEvent({\n      type: 'info',\n      description: `Mock decision recorded: ${JSON.stringify(decision)}`,\n    });\n    addFeedback('‚ÑπÔ∏è Mock decision logged. No backend action triggered.');\n    setInteractionNeeded(null);\n    setPendingDecision({});\n  };\n\n  const fetchInitialData = useCallback(async () => {\n    if (isMockSessionEnabled) {\n      return;\n    }\n\n    try {\n      const [personalitiesRes, opponentsRes, coursesRes] = await Promise.all([\n        fetch(`${SIMULATION_API_URL}/simulation/available-personalities`),\n        fetch(`${SIMULATION_API_URL}/simulation/suggested-opponents`),\n        fetch(`${SIMULATION_API_URL}/courses`)\n      ]);\n\n      const personalitiesData = await personalitiesRes.json();\n      const opponentsData = await opponentsRes.json();\n      const coursesData = await coursesRes.json();\n\n      setPersonalities(personalitiesData.personalities || []);\n      setSuggestedOpponents(opponentsData.opponents || []);\n      setCourses(coursesData || {});\n\n      if (opponentsData.opponents && opponentsData.opponents.length >= 3) {\n        setComputerPlayers([\n          { id: \"comp1\", ...opponentsData.opponents[0], is_human: false },\n          { id: \"comp2\", ...opponentsData.opponents[1], is_human: false },\n          { id: \"comp3\", ...opponentsData.opponents[2], is_human: false }\n        ]);\n      }\n    } catch (error) {\n      console.error(\"Error fetching initial data:\", error);\n    }\n  }, [isMockSessionEnabled, setComputerPlayers, setCourses, setPersonalities, setSuggestedOpponents]);\n\n  const fetchTurnBasedState = useCallback(async () => {\n    if (isMockSessionEnabled) {\n      return;\n    }\n\n    try {\n      const response = await fetch(`${SIMULATION_API_URL}/simulation/turn-based-state`);\n      const data = await response.json();\n\n      if (data.success) {\n        setTurnBasedState(data.turn_based_state);\n      }\n    } catch (error) {\n      console.error('Error fetching turn-based state:', error);\n    }\n  }, [isMockSessionEnabled, setTurnBasedState]);\n\n  useEffect(() => {\n    if (isMockSessionEnabled) {\n      hydrateMockSetup();\n      return;\n    }\n\n    fetchInitialData();\n  }, [fetchInitialData, hydrateMockSetup, isMockSessionEnabled]);\n  \n  // Fetch turn-based state when game is active\n  useEffect(() => {\n    if (isGameActive && useTurnBasedMode && !isMockSessionEnabled) {\n      fetchTurnBasedState();\n      const interval = setInterval(fetchTurnBasedState, 2000);\n      return () => clearInterval(interval);\n    }\n    return undefined;\n  }, [fetchTurnBasedState, isGameActive, isMockSessionEnabled, useTurnBasedMode]);\n  const startSimulation = async () => {\n    if (!isMockSessionEnabled && !humanPlayer.name.trim()) {\n      alert(\"Please enter your name\");\n      return;\n    }\n\n    setLoading(true);\n    try {\n      // Reset all local state for new simulation\n      setGameState(null);\n      endGame();  // Use endGame directly instead of setIsGameActive\n      clearFeedback();\n      setShotProbabilities(null);\n      setShotState(null);\n      setHasNextShot(true);\n      setInteractionNeeded(null);\n      setPendingDecision({});\n      setHoleDecisions({\n        action: null,\n        requested_partner: null,\n        offer_double: false,\n        accept_double: false\n      });\n      // GHIN lookup state reset removed - functionality not currently used\n\n      setMockStep(0);\n\n      if (isMockSessionEnabled) {\n        runMockSimulation();\n        setLoading(false);\n        return;\n      }\n\n      const response = await fetch(`${SIMULATION_API_URL}/simulation/setup`, {\n        method: \"POST\",\n        headers: { \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\" },\n        body: JSON.stringify({\n          human_player: humanPlayer,\n          computer_players: computerPlayers,\n          course_name: selectedCourse || null\n        })\n      });\n      \n      const data = await response.json();\n      if (data.status === \"ok\") {\n        // First set the game state\n        setGameState(data.game_state);\n        \n        // Then start the game with the new state\n        startGame(data.game_state);\n        \n        // Set initial feedback\n        clearFeedback();\n        if (data.feedback && Array.isArray(data.feedback)) {\n          data.feedback.forEach((msg) => addFeedback(msg));\n        } else {\n          addFeedback(data.message || \"Simulation started!\");\n        }\n        \n        // Set next shot availability from the response\n        if (data.next_shot_available !== undefined) {\n          setHasNextShot(data.next_shot_available);\n        } else {\n          setHasNextShot(true);  // Default to true after setup\n        }\n        \n        // Don't immediately play next shot - let the user initiate\n        // This prevents race conditions and gives user control\n      } else {\n        alert(\"Error starting simulation: \" + (formatErrorDetail(data.detail) || \"Unknown error\"));\n      }\n    } catch (error) {\n      console.error(\"Error starting simulation:\", error);\n      alert(\"Error starting simulation\");\n    } finally {\n      if (!isMockSessionEnabled) {\n        setLoading(false);\n      }\n    }\n  };\n\n  // Fetch timeline events from backend\n  const fetchTimelineEvents = async () => {\n    if (!isGameActive || isMockSessionEnabled) return;\n    \n    try {\n      setTimelineLoading(true);\n      const response = await fetch(`${SIMULATION_API_URL}/simulation/timeline`);\n      if (response.ok) {\n        const data = await response.json();\n        setTimelineEvents(data.events || []);\n      }\n    } catch (error) {\n      console.error(\"Error fetching timeline:\", error);\n    } finally {\n      setTimelineLoading(false);\n    }\n  };\n\n  // Fetch poker-style betting state\n  const fetchPokerState = async () => {\n    if (!isGameActive || isMockSessionEnabled) return;\n    \n    try {\n      const response = await fetch(`${SIMULATION_API_URL}/simulation/poker-state`);\n      if (response.ok) {\n        const data = await response.json();\n        setPokerState({\n          pot_size: data.pot_size,\n          base_bet: data.base_bet, \n          current_bet: data.current_bet,\n          betting_phase: data.betting_phase,\n          doubled: data.doubled,\n          players_in: data.players_in,\n          wagering_closed: data.wagering_closed\n        });\n        setBettingOptions(data.betting_options || []);\n      }\n    } catch (error) {\n      console.error(\"Error fetching poker state:\", error);\n    }\n  };\n\n  // Handle poker-style betting actions\n  const handleBettingAction = async (action, option) => {\n    if (isMockSessionEnabled) {\n      const label = option?.label || action;\n      const currentWager = gameState?.betting?.current_wager ?? gameState?.base_wager ?? 1;\n      const updatedWager = action === 'offer_double' ? currentWager * 2 : currentWager;\n\n      setGameState((previous) => {\n        if (!previous) {\n          return previous;\n        }\n\n        return {\n          ...previous,\n          betting: {\n            ...(previous.betting || {}),\n            current_wager: updatedWager,\n          },\n        };\n      });\n\n      setPokerState((previous) => ({\n        ...previous,\n        current_wager:\n          action === 'offer_double'\n            ? (previous?.current_wager ?? currentWager) * 2\n            : previous?.current_wager ?? updatedWager,\n        pending_actions: [],\n        last_mock_action: action,\n      }));\n\n      pushMockTimelineEvent({\n        type: action?.includes('double') ? 'double' : 'bet',\n        description: `Mock: ${label}`,\n      });\n\n      addFeedback(`üÉè Mock betting action captured: ${label}`);\n      return;\n    }\n\n    try {\n      setLoading(true);\n\n      const decision = {\n        decision_type: action,\n        player_id: 'human',\n        amount: option.amount || 0,\n        ...option\n      };\n\n      const response = await fetch(`${SIMULATION_API_URL}/simulation/betting-decision`, {\n        method: 'POST',\n        headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },\n        body: JSON.stringify(decision)\n      });\n\n      if (response.ok) {\n        const result = await response.json();\n        if (result.success) {\n          // Update game state if provided\n          if (result.game_state) {\n            setGameState(result.game_state);\n          }\n\n          // Refresh timeline and poker state\n          await Promise.all([fetchTimelineEvents(), fetchPokerState()]);\n        }\n      }\n    } catch (error) {\n      console.error(\"Error handling betting action:\", error);\n    } finally {\n      setLoading(false);\n    }\n  };\n\n  // Auto-refresh timeline and poker state when game is active\n  useEffect(() => {\n    if (isGameActive && !isMockSessionEnabled) {\n      // Initial fetch\n      fetchTimelineEvents();\n      fetchPokerState();\n\n      // Set up polling for real-time updates\n      const interval = setInterval(() => {\n        fetchTimelineEvents();\n        fetchPokerState();\n      }, 3000); // Update every 3 seconds\n\n      return () => clearInterval(interval);\n    }\n    // eslint-disable-next-line react-hooks/exhaustive-deps\n  }, [isGameActive, gameState?.current_hole, gameState?.hole_state?.current_shot_number]); // fetchTimelineEvents and fetchPokerState are stable\n  \n  // Removed unused testNewEndpoints function\n\n  // Add the missing makeDecision function and improve interactive flow\n  const makeDecision = async (decision) => {\n    if (isMockSessionEnabled) {\n      handleMockDecision(decision);\n      return;\n    }\n\n    setLoading(true);\n    try {\n      // Determine which endpoint to use based on decision type\n      let endpoint = '/simulation/play-hole';\n      let payload = { ...decision };\n      \n      // Handle different decision types\n      if (decision.action === 'request_partner' || decision.action === 'go_solo' || decision.action === 'keep_watching') {\n        // Captain decisions during tee shots\n        endpoint = '/simulation/play-hole';\n        payload = {\n          action: decision.action,\n          requested_partner: decision.requested_partner || decision.partner_id\n        };\n      } else if (decision.accept_partnership !== undefined) {\n        // Partnership response\n        endpoint = '/simulation/play-hole';\n        payload = {\n          accept_partnership: decision.accept_partnership\n        };\n      } else if (decision.offer_double !== undefined) {\n        // Doubling decisions\n        endpoint = '/simulation/betting-decision';\n        payload = {\n          action: decision.offer_double ? 'offer_double' : 'decline_double'\n        };\n      } else if (decision.accept_double !== undefined) {\n        // Double response\n        endpoint = '/simulation/betting-decision';\n        payload = {\n          action: decision.accept_double ? 'accept_double' : 'decline_double'\n        };\n      }\n\n      const response = await fetch(`${SIMULATION_API_URL}${endpoint}`, {\n        method: \"POST\",\n        headers: { \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\" },\n        body: JSON.stringify(payload)\n      });\n      \n      if (!response.ok) {\n        const errorText = await response.text();\n        throw new Error(`Backend error: ${response.status} - ${errorText}`);\n      }\n      \n      const data = await response.json();\n      \n      if (data.status === \"ok\") {\n        // Update game state\n        setGameState(data.game_state);\n        \n        // Add feedback messages\n        if (data.feedback && Array.isArray(data.feedback)) {\n          data.feedback.forEach(msg => addFeedback(msg));\n        } else if (data.decision_result?.message) {\n          addFeedback(`üí∞ ${data.decision_result.message}`);\n        }\n        \n        // Handle interaction needed\n        if (data.interaction_needed) {\n          setInteractionNeeded(data.interaction_needed);\n        } else {\n          setInteractionNeeded(null);\n          setPendingDecision({});\n        }\n        \n        // Update shot state if available\n        if (data.next_shot_available !== undefined) {\n          setHasNextShot(data.next_shot_available);\n        }\n        \n        const baseProbabilities =\n          data.probabilities && typeof data.probabilities === \"object\" && !Array.isArray(data.probabilities)\n            ? data.probabilities\n            : null;\n\n        const bettingAnalysis =\n          data.betting_probabilities && typeof data.betting_probabilities === \"object\"\n            ? data.betting_probabilities\n            : null;\n\n        if (baseProbabilities || bettingAnalysis) {\n          const combinedProbabilities = {\n            ...(baseProbabilities || {}),\n            ...(bettingAnalysis ? { betting_analysis: bettingAnalysis } : {}),\n          };\n\n          setShotProbabilities(combinedProbabilities);\n        }\n        \n        // Auto-continue if no interaction needed and shots available\n        if (!data.interaction_needed && data.next_shot_available) {\n          // Small delay to let user see the feedback\n          setTimeout(() => {\n            if (!loading && !interactionNeeded) {\n              playNextShot();\n            }\n          }, 1500);\n        }\n        \n      } else {\n        throw new Error(data.message || 'Unknown error occurred');\n      }\n      \n    } catch (error) {\n      console.error(\"Error making decision:\", error);\n      \n      // Provide user-friendly error messages\n      let errorMessage = \"Error making decision: \";\n      if (error.message.includes(\"Backend error: 500\")) {\n        errorMessage += \"Server error - please try again\";\n      } else if (error.message.includes(\"Backend error: 400\")) {\n        errorMessage += \"Invalid decision - please check your choice\";\n      } else if (error.message.includes(\"fetch\")) {\n        errorMessage += \"Network error - check your connection\";\n      } else {\n        errorMessage += error.message;\n      }\n      \n      // Add error to feedback instead of alert\n      addFeedback(`‚ùå ${errorMessage}`);\n      \n      // Clear interaction needed to prevent stuck state\n      setInteractionNeeded(null);\n    } finally {\n      setLoading(false);\n    }\n  };\n  \n  const playNextShot = async () => {\n    if (loading || interactionNeeded) {\n      if (process.env.NODE_ENV !== 'production') {\n        console.debug(\"Cannot play shot:\", { loading, interactionNeeded });\n      }\n      return;\n    }\n\n    if (isMockSessionEnabled) {\n      const presetName = mockStep % 2 === 0 ? 'pressureDouble' : SIMULATION_MOCK_PRESET;\n      const nextPreset = getSimulationMock(presetName);\n\n      pushMockTimelineEvent({\n        type: 'shot',\n        description:\n          nextPreset.shotState?.recommended_shot ||\n          `Mock shot progression ${mockStep + 1}.`,\n      });\n\n      addFeedback(`üéØ Mock shot advanced (step ${mockStep + 1}).`);\n\n      setGameState((previous) => {\n        if (!previous) {\n          return nextPreset.gameState || previous;\n        }\n\n        const nextHoleState = {\n          ...(previous.hole_state || {}),\n          ...((nextPreset.gameState && nextPreset.gameState.hole_state) || {}),\n          current_shot_number:\n            (previous.hole_state?.current_shot_number || 0) + 1,\n        };\n\n        return {\n          ...previous,\n          ...(nextPreset.gameState || {}),\n          hole_state: nextHoleState,\n        };\n      });\n\n      setShotState(nextPreset.shotState || null);\n      setShotProbabilities(nextPreset.shotProbabilities || null);\n      setInteractionNeeded(nextPreset.interactionNeeded || null);\n      setBettingOptions(nextPreset.bettingOptions || bettingOptions);\n      setPokerState((previous) => ({\n        ...previous,\n        ...nextPreset.pokerState,\n      }));\n      setHasNextShot(\n        nextPreset.hasNextShot !== undefined\n          ? Boolean(nextPreset.hasNextShot)\n          : false\n      );\n      setMockStep((previous) => previous + 1);\n      return;\n    }\n\n    setLoading(true);\n    try {\n      const response = await fetch(`${SIMULATION_API_URL}/simulation/play-next-shot`, {\n        method: \"POST\",\n        headers: { \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\" },\n        body: JSON.stringify(pendingDecision)\n      });\n      \n      if (!response.ok) {\n        const errorText = await response.text();\n        throw new Error(`Backend error: ${response.status} - ${errorText}`);\n      }\n      \n      const data = await response.json();\n      \n      if (data.status === \"ok\") {\n        setGameState(data.game_state);\n        \n        // Add feedback from the shot simulation\n        if (data.feedback && data.feedback.length > 0) {\n          data.feedback.forEach(msg => addFeedback(msg));\n        }\n        \n        // Handle shot result\n        if (data.shot_result) {\n          addFeedback(`üéØ Shot Result: ${JSON.stringify(data.shot_result)}`);\n        }\n        \n        // Handle interaction needed\n        if (data.interaction_needed) {\n          setInteractionNeeded(data.interaction_needed);\n          setPendingDecision({});\n        } else {\n          setInteractionNeeded(null);\n          setPendingDecision({});\n        }\n        \n        // Update next shot availability\n        setHasNextShot(data.next_shot_available);\n        \n        // Refresh timeline and poker state after shot\n        await Promise.all([fetchTimelineEvents(), fetchPokerState()]);\n        \n      } else {\n        throw new Error(data.message || 'Unknown error occurred');\n      }\n      \n    } catch (error) {\n      console.error(\"Error playing next shot:\", error);\n      \n      let errorMessage = \"Error playing shot: \";\n      if (error.message.includes(\"Backend error: 500\")) {\n        errorMessage += \"Server error - please try again\";\n      } else if (error.message.includes(\"fetch\")) {\n        errorMessage += \"Network error - check your connection\";\n      } else {\n        errorMessage += error.message;\n      }\n      \n      addFeedback(`‚ùå ${errorMessage}`);\n    } finally {\n      setLoading(false);\n    }\n  };\n  \n  const resetSimulation = () => {\n    setGameState(null);\n    endGame();  // Use endGame directly instead of setIsGameActive\n    clearFeedback();\n    setHoleDecisions({\n      action: null,\n      requested_partner: null,\n      offer_double: false,\n      accept_double: false\n    });\n    setMockStep(0);\n  };\n  \n  if (!isGameActive) {\n    return (\n      <GameSetup\n        humanPlayer={humanPlayer}\n        setHumanPlayer={setHumanPlayer}\n        computerPlayers={computerPlayers}\n        setComputerPlayers={setComputerPlayers}\n        selectedCourse={selectedCourse}\n        setSelectedCourse={setSelectedCourse}\n        courses={courses}\n        setCourses={setCourses}\n        personalities={personalities}\n        setPersonalities={setPersonalities}\n        suggestedOpponents={suggestedOpponents}\n        setSuggestedOpponents={setSuggestedOpponents}\n        onStartGame={startSimulation}\n      />\n    );\n  }\n\n  // Choose interface based on mode preference\n  if (useTurnBasedMode && turnBasedState) {\n    return (\n      <TurnBasedInterface\n        gameState={{\n          ...gameState,\n          ...(turnBasedState.turn_based_state || turnBasedState),\n          interactionNeeded,\n          hasNextShot,\n          feedback\n        }}\n        onMakeDecision={makeDecision}\n        interactionNeeded={interactionNeeded}\n        feedback={feedback}\n        shotState={shotState}\n        onNextShot={playNextShot}\n        hasNextShot={hasNextShot}\n      />\n    );\n  }\n  \n  // Use Enhanced Simulation Layout with Timeline and Poker Betting\n  const useEnhancedLayout = true; // TODO: Make this a user preference\n\n  if (useEnhancedLayout) {\n    return (\n      <EnhancedSimulationLayout\n        gameState={gameState}\n        shotState={shotState}\n        probabilities={shotProbabilities}\n        onDecision={makeDecision}\n        onPlayNextShot={playNextShot}\n        timelineEvents={timelineEvents}\n        timelineLoading={timelineLoading}\n        pokerState={pokerState}\n        bettingOptions={bettingOptions}\n        onBettingAction={handleBettingAction}\n        currentPlayer=\"human\"\n        interactionNeeded={interactionNeeded}\n        hasNextShot={hasNextShot}\n        feedback={feedback}\n      />\n    );\n  }\n\n  return (\n    <GamePlay\n      gameState={gameState}\n      onEndSimulation={resetSimulation}\n React, { useState, useEffect } from \"react\";\nimport CourseManager from \"./CourseManager\";\nimport PlayerProfileManager from \"../PlayerProfileManager\";\n// import usePlayerProfile from \"../../hooks/usePlayerProfile\"; // Temporarily disabled\n\nconst API_URL = process.env.REACT_APP_API_URL || \"\";\n\n// Helper function to safely serialize error details\nconst formatErrorDetail = (detail) => {\n  if (typeof detail === 'object' && detail !== null) {\n    return JSON.stringify(detail);\n  }\n  return detail;\n};\nconst COLORS = {\n  primary: \"#1976d2\",\n  accent: \"#00bcd4\",\n  warning: \"#ff9800\",\n  error: \"#d32f2f\",\n  success: \"#388e3c\",\n  bg: \"#f9fafe\",\n  card: \"#fff\",\n  border: \"#e0e0e0\",\n  text: \"#222\",\n  muted: \"#888\",\n};\nconst cardStyle = {\n  background: COLORS.card,\n  borderRadius: 12,\n  boxShadow: \"0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.04)\",\n  padding: 16,\n  marginBottom: 18,\n  border: `1px solid ${COLORS.border}`,\n};\nconst buttonStyle = {\n  background: COLORS.primary,\n  color: \"#fff\",\n  border: \"none\",\n  borderRadius: 8,\n  padding: \"14px 24px\",\n  fontWeight: 600,\n  fontSize: 18,\n  minHeight: 44,\n  margin: \"8px 0\",\n  boxShadow: \"0 1px 4px rgba(25, 118, 210, 0.08)\",\n  cursor: \"pointer\",\n  transition: \"background 0.2s\",\n};\nconst inputStyle = {\n  border: `1px solid ${COLORS.border}`,\n  borderRadius: 6,\n  padding: \"12px 16px\",\n  fontSize: 18,\n  minHeight: 44,\n  width: 60,\n  margin: \"4px 0\",\n};\n\nfunction GameSetupForm({ onSetup }) {\n  // Temporarily simplified profile handling\n  const selectedProfile = null;\n  const profiles = [];\n  const hasProfiles = false;\n  const selectProfile = () => {};\n\n  const [players, setPlayers] = useState([\n    { id: 'p1', name: '', handicap: '', strength: '', is_human: true, profile_id: null },\n    { id: 'p2', name: '', handicap: '', strength: '', is_human: true, profile_id: null },\n    { id: 'p3', name: '', handicap: '', strength: '', is_human: true, profile_id: null },\n    { id: 'p4', name: '', handicap: '', strength: '', is_human: true, profile_id: null },\n  ]);\n  const [courses, setCourses] = useState([]);\n  const [courseName, setCourseName] = useState('');\n  const [error, setError] = useState('');\n  const [showCourseManager, setShowCourseManager] = useState(false);\n  const [showProfileManager, setShowProfileManager] = useState(false);\n  const [setupMode, setSetupMode] = useState('quick'); // 'quick' or 'profile'\n  // GHIN lookup state\n  const [ghinSearch, setGhinSearch] = useState({}); // {p1: {first_name, last_name}, ...}\n  const [ghinResults, setGhinResults] = useState({}); // {p1: [], ...}\n  const [ghinLoading, setGhinLoading] = useState({});\n  const [ghinError, setGhinError] = useState({});\n\n  useEffect(() => {\n    fetch(`${API_URL}/courses`)\n      .then(res => {\n        if (!res.ok) {\n          throw new Error(`HTTP ${res.status}: ${res.statusText}`);\n        }\n        return res.json();\n      })\n      .then(data => {\n        if (!data || typeof data !== 'object') {\n          throw new Error('Invalid courses data format');\n        }\n        \n        const courseNames = Object.keys(data);\n        setCourses(courseNames);\n        \n        if (courseNames.length > 0) {\n          setCourseName(courseNames[0]);\n        } else {\n          throw new Error('No courses available');\n        }\n      })\n      .catch(error => {\n        console.error('Failed to load courses:', error);\n        \n        // Provide fallback courses so game can still start\n        const fallbackCourses = [\"Default Course\"];\n        setCourses(fallbackCourses);\n        setCourseName(\"Default Course\");\n        \n        // Set error to show user-friendly message\n        setError('Unable to load courses from server. Using default course. The game can still be played.');\n        \n        // Clear error after 5 seconds to not permanently block the UI\n        setTimeout(() => {\n          setError('');\n        }, 5000);\n      });\n  }, []);\n\n  // Auto-populate first player with selected profile\n  useEffect(() => {\n    if (selectedProfile && setupMode === 'profile') {\n      setPlayers(prevPlayers => prevPlayers.map((p, i) => \n        i === 0 ? {\n          ...p,\n          name: selectedProfile.name,\n          handicap: selectedProfile.handicap.toString(),\n          strength: getStrengthFromHandicap(selectedProfile.handicap),\n          profile_id: selectedProfile.id\n        } : p\n      ));\n    }\n  }, [selectedProfile, setupMode]);\n\n  const getStrengthFromHandicap = (handicap) => {\n    const h = parseFloat(handicap);\n    if (h <= 5) return 'Expert';\n    if (h <= 10) return 'Strong';\n    if (h <= 15) return 'Average';\n    return 'Beginner';\n  };\n\n  const handleChange = (idx, field, value) => {\n    setPlayers(players => players.map((p, i) => i === idx ? { ...p, [field]: value } : p));\n  };\n\n  const handleProfileSelect = (idx, profile) => {\n    if (profile) {\n      setPlayers(prevPlayers => prevPlayers.map((p, i) => \n        i === idx ? {\n          ...p,\n          name: profile.name,\n          handicap: profile.handicap.toString(),\n          strength: getStrengthFromHandicap(profile.handicap),\n          profile_id: profile.id\n        } : p\n      ));\n    } else {\n      setPlayers(prevPlayers => prevPlayers.map((p, i) => \n        i === idx ? {\n          ...p,\n          name: '',\n          handicap: '',\n          strength: '',\n          profile_id: null\n        } : p\n      ));\n    }\n  };\n\n  // GHIN lookup handlers\n  const handleGhinSearchChange = (pid, field, value) => {\n    setGhinSearch(s => ({ ...s, [pid]: { ...s[pid], [field]: value } }));\n  };\n  const handleGhinLookup = async (pid) => {\n    const search = ghinSearch[pid] || {};\n    if (!search.last_name || !search.last_name.trim()) return;\n    setGhinLoading(l => ({ ...l, [pid]: true }));\n    setGhinError(e => ({ ...e, [pid]: '' }));\n    setGhinResults(r => ({ ...r, [pid]: [] }));\n    try {\n      const params = new URLSearchParams({\n        last_name: search.last_name,\n        ...(search.first_name ? { first_name: search.first_name } : {})\n      });\n      const res = await fetch(`${API_URL}/ghin/lookup?${params.toString()}`);\n      if (!res.ok) throw new Error('Lookup failed');\n      const data = await res.json();\n      setGhinResults(r => ({ ...r, [pid]: data }));\n    } catch (err) {\n      setGhinError(e => ({ ...e, [pid]: err.message }));\n    } finally {\n      setGhinLoading(l => ({ ...l, [pid]: false }));\n    }\n  };\n  const handleGhinSelect = (pid, golfer) => {\n    setPlayers(players => players.map(p => p.id === pid ? {\n      ...p,\n      name: golfer.name,\n      handicap: golfer.handicap || '',\n      is_human: true  // All players in GameSetupForm are human\n    } : p));\n    setGhinResults(r => ({ ...r, [pid]: [] }));\n    setGhinSearch(s => ({ ...s, [pid]: '' }));\n  };\n\n  const handleSubmit = async e => {\n    e.preventDefault();\n    if (players.some(p => !p.name || p.handicap === '' || !p.strength)) {\n      setError('All names, handicaps, and strengths are required.');\n      return;\n    }\n    setError('');\n    const res = await fetch(`${API_URL}/game/setup`, {\n      method: 'POST',\n      headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },\n      body: JSON.stringify({ players, course_name: courseName }),\n    });\n    const data = await res.json();\n    if (data.status === 'ok') {\n      onSetup(data.game_state);\n    } else {\n      setError(formatErrorDetail(data.detail) || 'Setup failed');\n    }\n  };\n\n  return (\n    <>\n      {showCourseManager && <CourseManager onClose={() => setShowCourseManager(false)} onCoursesChanged={() => {\n        fetch(`${API_URL}/courses`)\n          .then(res => {\n            if (!res.ok) {\n              throw new Error(`HTTP ${res.status}: ${res.statusText}`);\n            }\n            return res.json();\n          })\n          .then(data => {\n            if (data && typeof data === 'object') {\n              setCourses(Object.keys(data));\n            }\n          })\n          .catch(error => {\n            console.error('Failed to refresh courses:', error);\n            setError('Failed to refresh courses from server.');\n            setTimeout(() => setError(''), 3000);\n          });\n      }} />}\n      {showProfileManager && (\n        <div style={{ position: 'fixed', top: 0, left: 0, right: 0, bottom: 0, backgroundColor: 'rgba(0,0,0,0.5)', zIndex: 1000, display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', justifyContent: 'center' }}>\n          <div style={{ backgroundColor: 'white', borderRadius: 12, maxWidth: '90vw', maxHeight: '90vh', overflow: 'auto', padding: 20 }}>\n            <PlayerProfileManager \n              onProfileSelect={(profile) => {\n                selectProfile(profile);\n                setShowProfileManager(false);\n              }}\n              selectedProfile={selectedProfile}\n              showSelector={false}\n            />\n            <button \n              onClick={() => setShowProfileManager(false)}\n              style={{ ...buttonStyle, background: COLORS.muted, marginTop: 16 }}\n            >\n              Close\n            </button>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n      )}\n      <form onSubmit={handleSubmit} style={{ ...cardStyle, maxWidth: 480, margin: '40px auto', background: COLORS.bg }}>\n        <h2 style={{ color: COLORS.primary, marginBottom: 12 }}>Setup Players & Course</h2>\n        \n        {/* Setup Mode Toggle */}\n        <div style={{ marginBottom: 16, display: 'flex', gap: 8, alignItems: 'center' }}>\n          <label style={{ fontWeight: 600 }}>Setup Mode:</label>\n          <button\n            type=\"button\"\n            onClick={() => setSetupMode('quick')}\n            style={{\n              ...buttonStyle,\n              padding: '8px 16px',\n              fontSize: 14,\n              background: setupMode === 'quick' ? COLORS.primary : COLORS.muted\n            }}\n          >\n            Quick Setup\n          </button>\n          <button\n            type=\"button\"\n            onClick={() => setSetupMode('profile')}\n            style={{\n              ...buttonStyle,\n              padding: '8px 16px',\n              fontSize: 14,\n              background: setupMode === 'profile' ? COLORS.primary : COLORS.muted\n            }}\n          >\n            Use Profiles\n          </button>\n          <button\n            type=\"button\"\n            onClick={() => setShowProfileManager(true)}\n            style={{\n              ...buttonStyle,\n              padding: '8px 16px',\n              fontSize: 14,\n              background: COLORS.accent\n            }}\n          >\n            Manage Profiles\n          </button>\n        </div>\n\n        {/* Profile Selection for Profile Mode */}\n        {setupMode === 'profile' && (\n          <div style={{ marginBottom: 16, padding: 12, backgroundColor: '#f8f9fa', borderRadius: 8, border: '1px solid #e9ecef' }}>\n            <h4 style={{ margin: '0 0 8px 0', color: COLORS.primary }}>Your Profile</h4>\n            {selectedProfile ? (\n              <div style={{ display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', justifyContent: 'space-between' }}>\n                <div>\n                  <strong>{selectedProfile.name}</strong> (Handicap: {selectedProfile.handicap})\n                </div>\n                <button\n                  type=\"button\"\n                  onClick={() => selectProfile(null)}\n                  style={{ ...buttonStyle, padding: '4px 8px', fontSize: 12, background: COLORS.warning }}\n                >\n                  Change\n                </button>\n              </div>\n            ) : (\n              <div>\n                <p style={{ margin: '0 0 8px 0', color: COLORS.muted }}>No profile selected</p>\n                {hasProfiles ? (\n                  <div style={{ display: 'flex', flexWrap: 'wrap', gap: 8 }}>\n                    {profiles.slice(0, 3).map(profile => (\n                      <button\n                        key={profile.id}\n                        type=\"button\"\n                        onClick={() => selectProfile(profile)}\n                        style={{ ...buttonStyle, padding: '6px 12px', fontSize: 12, background: COLORS.accent }}\n                      >\n                        {profile.name}\n                      </button>\n                    ))}\n                  </div>\n                ) : (\n                  <p style={{ margin: 0, color: COLORS.muted, fontSize: 14 }}>\n                    Create a profile to track your statistics across games.\n                  </p>\n                )}\n              </div>\n            )}\n          </div>\n        )}\n        <div style={{ marginBottom: 12, display: 'flex', flexWrap: 'wrap', gap: 8, flexDirection: window.innerWidth < 600 ? 'column' : 'row' }}>\n          <label style={{ fontWeight: 600, marginRight: 8 }}>Course:</label>\n          <select style={{ ...inputStyle, width: 180 }} value={courseName} onChange={e => setCourseName(e.target.value)}>\n            {courses.map(c => <option key={c} value={c}>{c}</option>)}\n          </select>\n          <button type=\"button\" style={{ ...buttonStyle, background: COLORS.accent, marginLeft: 10, fontSize: 16, padding: \"10px 18px\" }} onClick={() => setShowCourseManager(true)}>Manage Courses</button>\n        </div>\n        {players.map((player, idx) => (\n          <div key={player.id} style={{ marginBottom: 18, border: '1px solid #eee', borderRadius: 8, padding: 12 }}>\n            {/* Profile Selection for Profile Mode */}\n            {setupMode === 'profile' && idx > 0 && (\n              <div style={{ marginBottom: 12 }}>\n                <label style={{ display: 'block', fontSize: 12, fontWeight: 600, marginBottom: 4 }}>\n                  Player {idx + 1} Profile (Optional):\n                </label>\n                <select\n                  value={player.profile_id || ''}\n                  onChange={e => {\n                    const profileId = e.target.value;\n                    const selectedProfile = profiles.find(p => p.id === parseInt(profileId));\n                    handleProfileSelect(idx, selectedProfile);\n                  }}\n                  style={{ width: '100%', marginBottom: 8 }}\n                >\n                  <option value=\"\">Manual Entry</option>\n                  {profiles.map(profile => (\n                    <option key={profile.id} value={profile.id}>\n                      {profile.name} (Handicap: {profile.handicap})\n                    </option>\n                  ))}\n                </select>\n              </div>\n            )}\n            \n            <div style={{ display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: 8, flexWrap: 'wrap' }}>\n              <label htmlFor={`player-${idx}-name`} style={{ fontSize: 12, fontWeight: 600 }}>\n                Player {idx + 1} Name\n              </label>\n              <input\n                type=\"text\"\n                placeholder=\"Name\"\n                value={player.name}\n                onChange={e => handleChange(idx, 'name', e.target.value)}\n                style={{ width: 120, marginRight: 8 }}\n                id={`player-${idx}-name`}\n                disabled={setupMode === 'profile' && idx === 0 && selectedProfile}\n              />\n              <label htmlFor={`player-${idx}-handicap`} style={{ fontSize: 12, fontWeight: 600 }}>\n                Handicap\n              </label>\n              <input\n                type=\"number\"\n                placeholder=\"Handicap\"\n                value={player.handicap}\n                onChange={e => handleChange(idx, 'handicap', e.target.value)}\n                style={{ width: 70, marginRight: 8 }}\n                id={`player-${idx}-handicap`}\n                disabled={setupMode === 'profile' && idx === 0 && selectedProfile}\n              />\n              <select\n                value={player.strength}\n                onChange={e => handleChange(idx, 'strength', e.target.value)}\n                style={{ width: 110, marginRight: 8 }}\n                disabled={setupMode === 'profile' && ((idx === 0 && selectedProfile) || player.profile_id)}\n              >\n                <option value=\"\">Strength</option>\n                <option value=\"Beginner\">Beginner</option>\n                <option value=\"Average\">Average</option>\n                <option value=\"Strong\">Strong</option>\n                <option value=\"Expert\">Expert</option>\n              </select>\n              \n              {/* Profile indicator */}\n              {player.profile_id && (\n                <span style={{ fontSize: 12, color: COLORS.success, fontWeight: 600 }}>\n                  üìä Profile\n                </span>\n              )}\n              {/* GHIN Lookup UI */}\n              <input type=\"text\" placeholder=\"First Name (optional)\" value={ghinSearch[player.id]?.first_name || ''} onChange={e => handleGhinSearchChange(player.id, 'first_name', e.target.value)} />\n              <input type=\"text\" placeholder=\"Last Name (required)\" value={ghinSearch[player.id]?.last_name || ''} onChange={e => handleGhinSearchChange(player.id, 'last_name', e.target.value)} required />\n              <button type=\"button\" onClick={() => handleGhinLookup(player.id)} disabled={ghinLoading?.[player.id] || !ghinSearch[player.id]?.last_name} style={{ marginRight: 4 }}>\n                {ghinLoading?.[player.id] ? 'Searching...' : 'GHIN Lookup'}\n              </button>\n            </div>\n            {ghinError?.[player.id] && <div style={{ color: 'red', fontSize: 13 }}>{ghinError[player.id]}</div>}\n            {ghinResults?.[player.id]?.length > 0 && (\n              <div style={{ marginTop: 6, background: '#f9f9f9', border: '1px solid #ddd', borderRadius: 6, padding: 8 }}>\n                <div style={{ fontSize: 13, marginBottom: 4 }}>Select a golfer:</div>\n                {ghinResults[player.id].map(golfer => (\n                  <div key={golfer.ghin} style={{ padding: 4, cursor: 'pointer', borderBottom: '1px solid #eee' }} onClick={() => handleGhinSelect(player.id, golfer)}>\n                    <strong>{golfer.name}</strong> (GHIN: {golfer.ghin})<br />\n                    Club: {golfer.club} | Handicap: {golfer.handicap ?? React, { useState, useEffect, useCallback } from 'react';\nimport ghinService, { initializeGHIN } from '../services/ghinService';\n\nconst WGPAnalyticsDashboard = () => {\n  const [leaderboardData, setLeaderboardData] = useState([]);\n  const [topBestScores, setTopBestScores] = useState([]);\n  const [topWorstScores, setTopWorstScores] = useState([]);\n  const [mostRoundsPlayed, setMostRoundsPlayed] = useState([]);\n  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(true);\n  const [ghinLoading, setGhinLoading] = useState(false);\n  const [ghinData, setGhinData] = useState({});\n  const [ghinEnabled, setGhinEnabled] = useState(false);\n\n  const calculateQB = useCallback((player, rank) => {\n    const totalPlayers = 28;\n    return totalPlayers * 10 + (totalPlayers - rank) * 10;\n  }, []);\n\n  const processLeaderboardData = useCallback((data) => {\n    const sortedByQuarters = [...data].sort((a, b) => b.total_earnings - a.total_earnings);\n\n    const leaderboard = sortedByQuarters.map((player, index) => ({\n      ...player,\n      quarters: Math.round(player.total_earnings),\n      average: player.games_played > 0 ? Math.round(player.total_earnings / player.games_played) : 0,\n      rounds: player.games_played,\n      qb: calculateQB(player, index)\n    }));\n\n    setLeaderboardData(leaderboard);\n\n    const bestScores = [...leaderboard]\n      .filter(p => p.quarters > 0)\n      .sort((a, b) => b.quarters - a.quarters)\n      .slice(0, 5)\n      .map(p => ({\n        member: p.player_name,\n        topScore: p.quarters,\n        date: '27-Jul'\n      }));\n    setTopBestScores(bestScores);\n\n    const worstScores = [...leaderboard]\n      .filter(p => p.quarters < 0)\n      .sort((a, b) => a.quarters - b.quarters)\n      .slice(0, 5)\n      .map(p => ({\n        member: p.player_name,\n        score: p.quarters,\n        date: '23-Aug'\n      }));\n    setTopWorstScores(worstScores);\n\n    const roundsPlayed = [...leaderboard]\n      .sort((a, b) => b.rounds - a.rounds)\n      .map(p => ({\n        member: p.player_name,\n        rounds: p.rounds,\n        banquet: p.rounds >= 20\n      }));\n    setMostRoundsPlayed(roundsPlayed);\n  }, [calculateQB]);\n\n  const fetchGHINData = useCallback(async (players) => {\n    if (!ghinService.isInitialized()) {\n      return;\n    }\n\n    try {\n      setGhinLoading(true);\n      const ghinDataMap = {};\n\n      const playersWithMockGHINIds = players.map(player => ({\n        ...player,\n        ghinId: `GHIN${player.player_name.replace(/\\s/g, '').toUpperCase()}`\n      }));\n\n      const batchResults = await ghinService.getBatchGolferInfo(\n        playersWithMockGHINIds.map(p => p.ghinId)\n      );\n\n      batchResults.success.forEach(ghinInfo => {\n        const player = playersWithMockGHINIds.find(p => p.ghinId === ghinInfo.ghinId);\n        if (player) {\n          ghinDataMap[player.player_name] = {\n            handicapIndex: ghinInfo.handicapIndex,\n            recentScores: ghinInfo.recentScores,\n            lastUpdated: ghinInfo.lastUpdated,\n            club: ghinInfo.club\n          };\n        }\n      });\n\n      setGhinData(ghinDataMap);\n      if (process.env.NODE_ENV !== 'production') {\n        console.debug(`Fetched GHIN data for ${Object.keys(ghinDataMap).length} players`);\n      }\n\n    } catch (error) {\n      console.error('Error fetching GHIN data:', error);\n    } finally {\n      setGhinLoading(false);\n    }\n  }, []);\n\n  const fetchAnalytics = useCallback(async () => {\n    try {\n      setLoading(true);\n      \n      const API_URL = process.env.REACT_APP_API_URL || \"http://localhost:8000\";\n      \n      // Always use GHIN-enhanced leaderboard (shows stored handicap data even if GHIN API is offline)\n      const leaderboardUrl = `${API_URL}/leaderboard/ghin-enhanced`;\n      \n      const leaderboardResponse = await fetch(leaderboardUrl, {\n        method: 'GET',\n        headers: {\n          'Content-Type': 'application/json',\n        }\n      });\n      \n      if (!leaderboardResponse.ok) {\n        throw new Error(`Failed to fetch leaderboard data: ${leaderboardResponse.statusText}`);\n      }\n      \n      const leaderboardData = await leaderboardResponse.json();\n      \n      // If no data available, show empty state\n      if (!leaderboardData || leaderboardData.length === 0) {\n        setLeaderboardData([]);\n        setTopBestScores([]);\n        setTopWorstScores([]);\n        setMostRoundsPlayed([]);\n        return;\n      }\n      \n      // Process leaderboard data from database (filter out Grand Total if it exists)\n      const leaderboard = leaderboardData\n        .filter(player => {\n          const name = (player.player_name || player.name || '').toLowerCase();\n          return name !== 'grand total' && name !== 'total' && name !== '';\n        })\n        .map(player => ({\n          player_name: player.player_name || player.name,\n          games_played: player.games_played || 0,\n          games_won: player.games_won || 0,\n          win_rate: player.win_percentage ? player.win_percentage / 100 : 0,\n          total_earnings: player.total_earnings || 0,\n          avg_earnings_per_game: player.avg_earnings || 0,\n          best_finish: player.best_finish || 99,\n          holes_won: player.holes_won || 0,\n          partnerships: player.partnerships_formed || 0,\n          partnership_success: player.partnership_success ? player.partnership_success / 100 : 0,\n          betting_success: player.betting_success || 0,\n          solo_attempts: player.solo_attempts || 0,\n          solo_wins: player.solo_wins || 0,\n          // GHIN data (if available from enhanced endpoint)\n          handicap: player.handicap,\n          ghin_id: player.ghin_id,\n          ghin_data: player.ghin_data,\n          recent_form: player.recent_form\n        }));\n      \n      // Process and format data\n      processLeaderboardData(leaderboard);\n      \n      // Fetch GHIN data if available\n      if (ghinEnabled && leaderboard.length > 0) {\n        fetchGHINData(leaderboard);\n      }\n      \n    } catch (error) {\n      console.error('Error fetching analytics:', error);\n    } finally {\n      setLoading(false);\n    }\n  }, [fetchGHINData, ghinEnabled, processLeaderboardData]);\n\n  const initializeServices = useCallback(async () => {\n    try {\n      const ghinInitialized = await initializeGHIN();\n      setGhinEnabled(ghinInitialized);\n      if (process.env.NODE_ENV !== 'production') {\n        if (ghinInitialized) {\n          console.debug('GHIN service initialized successfully');\n        } else {\n          console.debug('GHIN service not available - continuing without GHIN integration');\n        }\n      }\n    } catch (error) {\n      console.error('Failed to initialize GHIN service:', error);\n      setGhinEnabled(false);\n    }\n  }, []);\n\n  useEffect(() => {\n    initializeServices();\n    fetchAnalytics();\n  }, [fetchAnalytics, initializeServices]);\n  if (loading) {\n    return (\n      <div className=\"min-h-screen bg-gray-50 p-8\">\n        <div className=\"max-w-7xl mx-auto\">\n          <div className=\"bg-white rounded-lg shadow p-8 text-center\">\n            <div className=\"animate-spin rounded-full h-12 w-12 border-b-2 border-blue-600 mx-auto mb-4\"></div>\n            <p className=\"text-gray-600\">Loading leaderboard data...</p>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    );\n  }\n\n  // Show empty state if no data\n  if (leaderboardData.length === 0) {\n    return (\n      <div className=\"min-h-screen bg-gray-50 p-8\">\n        <div className=\"max-w-7xl mx-auto\">\n          <div className=\"bg-white rounded-lg shadow p-8 text-center\">\n            <div className=\"text-6xl mb-4\">üìä</div>\n            <h2 className=\"text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4\">No Leaderboard Data Available</h2>\n            <p className=\"text-gray-600 mb-6\">\n              To display live leaderboard data, you need to set up Google Sheets synchronization.\n            </p>\n            <div className=\"bg-blue-50 p-6 rounded-lg mb-6\">\n              <h3 className=\"text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-3\">üîó Setup Instructions</h3>\n              <ol className=\"text-left space-y-2 text-sm text-blue-800\">\n                <li><strong>1.</strong> Go to the <a href=\"/live-sync\" className=\"underline\">Live Sync page</a></li>\n                <li><strong>2.</strong> Enter your Google Sheets URL</li>\n                <li><strong>3.</strong> Make sure your sheet is publicly viewable</li>\n                <li><strong>4.</strong> Click \"Sync Now\" to import your data</li>\n                <li><strong>5.</strong> Return here to view your leaderboard</li>\n              </ol>\n            </div>\n            <button \n              onClick={() => window.location.href = '/live-sync'}\n              className=\"px-6 py-3 bg-blue-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-blue-700 font-medium\"\n            >\n              Set Up Google Sheets Sync\n            </button>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    );\n  }\n\n  return (\n    <div className=\"min-h-screen bg-gray-50 p-4\">\n      <div className=\"max-w-full mx-auto\">\n        {/* Header */}\n        <div className=\"bg-white rounded-lg shadow mb-4 p-4\">\n          <h1 className=\"text-2xl font-bold text-center\">Wolf Goat Pig Leaderboard 2025-26 Season</h1>\n          <div className=\"text-center mt-1\">\n            <p className=\"text-gray-600\">Live data from Google Sheets sync</p>\n            {ghinEnabled && (\n              <div className=\"mt-1 flex justify-center items-center space-x-2\">\n                <span className=\"text-xs text-blue-600\">üèåÔ∏è GHIN Integration Active</span>\n                {ghinLoading && (\n                  <span className=\"text-xs text-blue-500 animate-pulse\">Syncing handicaps...</span>\n                )}\n              </div>\n            )}\n          </div>\n        </div>\n\n        {/* Main Grid Layout */}\n        <div className=\"grid grid-cols-12 gap-4\">\n          \n          {/* Main Leaderboard - Left Side (7 columns) */}\n          <div className=\"col-span-7\">\n            <div className=\"bg-white rounded-lg shadow overflow-hidden\">\n              <table className=\"min-w-full\">\n                <thead className=\"bg-gray-200\">\n                  <tr>\n                    <th className=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-xs font-medium text-gray-700\">Member</th>\n                    <th className=\"px-4 py-2 text-center text-xs font-medium text-gray-700\">Quarters</th>\n                    <th className=\"px-4 py-2 text-center text-xs font-medium text-gray-700\">Average</th>\n                    <th className=\"px-4 py-2 text-center text-xs font-medium @ts-nocheck\nimport React, { useState, useEffect } from 'react';\nimport { useTheme } from '../../theme/Provider';\nimport { Button, Card, Input, Select } from '../ui';\n\nconst API_URL = process.env.REACT_APP_API_URL || \"\";\n\ninterface Player {\n  id?: string;\n  name: string;\n  handicap: string;\n  personality?: string;\n  is_human: boolean;\n}\n\ninterface Course {\n  name: string;\n  holes: Array<{\n    hole_number: number;\n    par: number;\n    yards: number;\n    stroke_index: number;\n    description: string;\n  }>;\n  total_par: number;\n  total_yards: number;\n  hole_count: number;\n}\n\ninterface Personality {\n  id: string;\n  name: string;\n}\n\ninterface SuggestedOpponent {\n  name: string;\n  handicap: string;\n  personality: string;\n}\n\ninterface GhinGolfer {\n  name: string;\n  handicap: string;\n  club?: string;\n}\n\ninterface GameSetupProps {\n  humanPlayer: Player;\n  setHumanPlayer: React.Dispatch<React.SetStateAction<Player>>;\n  computerPlayers: Player[];\n  setComputerPlayers: React.Dispatch<React.SetStateAction<Player[]>>;\n  selectedCourse: string | null;\n  setSelectedCourse: React.Dispatch<React.SetStateAction<string | null>>;\n  courses: { [key: string]: Course };\n  setCourses: React.Dispatch<React.SetStateAction<{ [key: string]: Course }>>;\n  personalities?: Personality[];\n  setPersonalities: React.Dispatch<React.SetStateAction<Personality[]>>;\n  suggestedOpponents?: SuggestedOpponent[];\n  setSuggestedOpponents: React.Dispatch<React.SetStateAction<SuggestedOpponent[]>>;\n  onStartGame: () => void;\n}\n\nconst GameSetup: React.FC<GameSetupProps> = ({\n  humanPlayer,\n  setHumanPlayer,\n  computerPlayers,\n  setComputerPlayers,\n  selectedCourse,\n  setSelectedCourse,\n  courses,\n  setCourses,\n  personalities = [],\n  setPersonalities,\n  suggestedOpponents = [],\n  setSuggestedOpponents,\n  onStartGame\n}) => {\n  const theme = useTheme();\n  \n  // GHIN lookup modal state\n  const [ghinLookupSlot, setGhinLookupSlot] = useState<string | null>(null);\n  const [ghinLookupFirstName, setGhinLookupFirstName] = useState(\"\");\n  const [ghinLookupLastName, setGhinLookupLastName] = useState(\"\");\n  const [ghinLookupResults, setGhinLookupResults] = useState<GhinGolfer[]>([]);\n  const [ghinLookupLoading, setGhinLookupLoading] = useState(false);\n  const [ghinLookupError, setGhinLookupError] = useState(\"\");\n\n  useEffect(() => {\n    // Fetch courses with error handling\n    fetch(`${API_URL}/courses`)\n      .then(res => {\n        if (!res.ok) {\n          throw new Error(`HTTP ${res.status}: ${res.statusText}`);\n        }\n        return res.json();\n      })\n      .then((data: { [key: string]: Course }) => {\n        if (!data || typeof data !== 'object') {\n          throw new Error('Invalid courses data format');\n        }\n        setCourses(data);\n        \n        // Auto-select first course if none selected\n        if (!selectedCourse && Object.keys(data).length > 0) {\n          setSelectedCourse(Object.keys(data));\n        }\n      })\n      .catch(error => {\n        console.error('Failed to load courses:', error);\n        \n        // Provide fallback courses so game can still start\n        const fallbackCourses: { [key: string]: Course } = {\n          \"Default Course\": {\n            name: \"Default Course\",\n            holes: Array.from({length: 18}, (_, i) => ({\n              hole_number: i + 1,\n              par: 4,\n              yards: 400,\n              stroke_index: i + 1,\n              description: `Hole ${i + 1}`\n            })),\n            total_par: 72,\n            total_yards: 7200,\n            hole_count: 18\n          }\n        };\n        \n        setCourses(fallbackCourses);\n        setSelectedCourse(\"Default Course\");\n        \n        // Show user-friendly error message but don't block the game\n        alert('Unable to load courses from server. Using default course to continue the game.');\n      });\n    \n    // Fetch personalities with error handling\n    fetch(`${API_URL}/personalities`)\n      .then(res => {\n        if (!res.ok) {\n          throw new Error(`HTTP ${res.status}: ${res.statusText}`);\n        }\n        return res.json();\n      })\n      .then((data: Personality[]) => {\n        if (Array.isArray(data)) {\n          setPersonalities(data);\n        } else {\n          throw new Error('Invalid personalities data format');\n        }\n      })\n      .catch(error => {\n        console.error('Failed to load personalities:', error);\n        // Provide fallback personalities\n        const fallbackPersonalities: Personality[] = [\n          { id: 'aggressive', name: 'Aggressive' },\n          { id: 'conservative', name: 'Conservative' },\n          { id: 'balanced', name: 'Balanced' }\n        ];\n        setPersonalities(fallbackPersonalities);\n      });\n    \n    // Fetch suggested opponents with error handling\n    fetch(`${API_URL}/suggested_opponents`)\n      .then(res => {\n        if (!res.ok) {\n          throw new Error(`HTTP ${res.status}: ${res.statusText}`);\n        }\n        return res.json();\n      })\n      .then((data: SuggestedOpponent[]) => {\n        if (Array.isArray(data)) {\n          setSuggestedOpponents(data);\n        } else {\n          throw new Error('Invalid suggested opponents data format');\n        }\n      })\n      .catch(error => {\n        console.error('Failed to load suggested opponents:', error);\n        // Provide fallback suggested opponents\n        const fallbackOpponents: SuggestedOpponent[] = [\n          { name: 'Bob', handicap: '12', personality: 'aggressive' },\n          { name: 'Alice', handicap: '8', personality: 'conservative' },\n          { name: 'Charlie', handicap: '16', personality: 'balanced' }\n        ];\n        setSuggestedOpponents(fallbackOpponents);\n      });\n  }, [setCourses, setPersonalities, setSuggestedOpponents, selectedCourse, setSelectedCourse]);\n\n  // Initialize computer players if empty\n  useEffect(() => {\n    if (computerPlayers.length === 0) {\n      setComputerPlayers([\n        { id: \"comp1\", name: \"\", handicap: \"\", personality: \"\", is_human: false },\n        { id: \"comp2\", name: \"\", handicap: \"\", personality: \"\", is_human: false },\n        { id: \"comp3\", name: \"\", handicap: \"\", personality: \"\", is_human: false }\n      ]);\n    }\n  }, [computerPlayers, setComputerPlayers]);\n\n  const openGhinLookup = (slot: string) => {\n    setGhinLookupSlot(slot);\n    setGhinLookupFirstName(\"\");\n    setGhinLookupLastName(\"\");\n    setGhinLookupResults([]);\n    setGhinLookupLoading(false);\n    setGhinLookupError(\"\");\n  };\n\n  const closeGhinLookup = () => {\n    setGhinLookupSlot(null);\n  };\n\n  const doGhinLookup = async () => {\n    if (!ghinLookupLastName.trim()) {\n      setGhinLookupError(\"Last name required\");\n      return;\n    }\n    setGhinLookupLoading(true);\n    setGhinLookupError(\"\");\n    setGhinLookupResults([]);\n    try {\n      const params = new URLSearchParams({ \n        last_name: ghinLookupLastName, \n        first_name: ghinLookupFirstName \n      });\n      const res = await fetch(`${API_URL}/ghin/lookup?${params.toString()}`);\n      if (!res.ok) throw new Error(\"Lookup failed\");\n      const data: GhinGolfer[] = await res.json();\n      setGhinLookupResults(data);\n      if (data.length === 0) setGhinLookupError(\"No golfers found\");\n    } catch (err: any) {\n      setGhinLookupError(\"Lookup failed\");\n    } finally {\n      setGhinLookupLoading(false);\n    }\n  };\n\n  const selectGhinGolfer = (golfer: GhinGolfer) => {\n    if (ghinLookupSlot === \"human\") {\n      setHumanPlayer(h => ({ ...h, name: golfer.name, handicap: golfer.handicap || \"\", is_human: true }));\n    } else {\n      setComputerPlayers(players => players.map((p, i) => {\n        const slotId = `comp${i+1}`;\n        return slotId === ghinLookupSlot ? { ...p, name: golfer.name, handicap: golfer.handicap || \"\", is_human: false } : p;\n      }));\n    }\n    closeGhinLookup();\n  };\n\n  const loadSuggestedOpponent = (opponentData: SuggestedOpponent, index: number) => {\n    setComputerPlayers(players => players.map((p, i) => \n      i === index ? { ...p, ...opponentData, id: p.id } : p\n    ));\n  };\n\n  const validateAndStartGame = () => {\n    if (!humanPlayer.name.trim()) {\n      alert(\"Please enter your name\");\n      return;\n    }\n    \n    const invalidComputers = computerPlayers.filter(p => !p.name.trim() || !p.handicap);\n    if (invalidComputers.length > 0) {\n      alert(\"Please fill in all computer player details\");\n      return;\n    }\n    \n    if (!selectedCourse) {\n      alert(\"Please select a course\");\n      return;\n    }\n    \n    onStartGame();\n  };\n\n  return (\n    <div style={{ maxWidth: 800, margin: \"0 auto\", padding: 20 }}>\n      <Card>\n        <h2 style={{ color: theme.colors.primary, marginBottom: theme.spacing }}>\n          üéÆ Wolf Goat Pig Simulation Mode\n        </h2>\n        <p style={{ marginBottom: 20 }}>\n          Practice Wolf Goat Pig against computer opponents! This mode helps you learn the betting strategies\n          and get comfortable with the game mechanics. After each hole, you'll receive educational feedback\n          about your decisions.\n        </p>\n        \n        {/* Human Player Setup */}\n        <Card>\n          <h3>Your Details</h3>\n          <div style={{ display: \"grid\", gridTemplateColumns: \"1fr 1fr\", gap: 16 }}>\n            <Input\n              label=\"Your Name:\"\n              value={humanPlayer.name}\n              onChange={(e) => setHumanPlayer({...humanPlayer, name: e.target.value})}\n            />\n            <Input\n              label=\"Your Handicap:\"\n              type=\"number\"\n              value={humanPlayer.handicap}\n              onChange={(e) => setHumanPlayer({...humanPlayer, handicap: e.target.value})}\n            />\n          </div>\n          \n          <Button \n            variant=\"secondary\"\n            size=\"small\"\n            onClick={() => openGhinLookup(\"human\")}\n            style={{ marginTop: theme.spacing }}\n          >\n            Lookup GHIN Handicap\n          </Button>\n          \n          {ghinLookupSlot === \"human\" && (\n            <Card variant=\"info\" style={{ marginTop: theme.spacing }}>\n              <h4>GHIN Handicap Lookup</h4>\n              <Input\n                placeholder=\"First Name (optional)\"\n                value={ghinLookupFirstName}\n                onChange={e => setGhinLookupFirstName(e.target.value)}\n              />\n              <Input\n                placeholder=\"Last Name (required)\"\n                value={ghinLookupLastName}\n                onChange={e => setGhinLookupLastName(e.target.value)}\n              />\n              <div style={{ display: 'flex', gap: theme.spacing, marginTop: theme.spacing }}>\n                <Button \n                  size=\"small\"\n                  onClick={doGhinLookup} \n                  disabled={ghinLookupLoading}\n                >\n                  Search\n                </Button>\n                <Button \n                  variant=\"error\"\n                  size=\"small\"\n                  onClick={closeGhinLookup}\n                >\n                  Cancel\n                </Button>\n              </div>\n              \n              {ghinLookupLoading && <div style={{ color: theme.colors.textSecondary, marginTop: 8 }}>Searching...</div>}\n              {ghinLookupError && <div style={{ color: theme.colors.error, marginTop: 8 }}>{ghinLookupError}</div>}\n              \n              {ghinLookupResults.length > 0 && (\n                <div style={{ marginTop: theme.spacing }}>\n                  <h5>Results:</h5>\n                  {ghinLookupResults.map((g, idx) => (\n                    <div \n                      key={idx} \n                      style={{ \n                        padding: 8, \n                        border: `1px solid ${theme.colors.border}`, \n                        borderRadius: 6, \n                        marginBottom: 4, \n                        cursor: \"pointer\", \n                        background: theme.colors.paper \n                      }} \n                      onClick={() => selectGhinGolfer(g)}\n                    >\n                      <strong>{g.name}</strong> (H: {g.handicap}) \n                      {g.club && <span style={{ color: theme.colors.textSecondary }}>@ {g.club}</span>}\n                    </div>\n                  ))}\n                </div>\n              )}\n            </Card>\n          )}\n        </Card>\n\n        {/* Computer Players Setup */}\n        <Card>\n          <h3>Computer Opponents</h3>\n          {computerPlayers.map((player, index) => (\n            <Card key={index} variant=\"default\" style={{ marginBottom: 16 }}>\n              <h4>Computer Player {index + 1}</h4>\n              <div style={{ display: \"grid\", gridTemplateColumns: \"1fr 1fr\", gap: 16 }}>\n                <Input\n                  label=\"Name:\"\n                  value={player.name}\n                  onChange={(e) => {\n                    setComputerPlayers(players => players.map((p, i) => \n                      i === index ? { ...p, name: e.target.value } : p\n                    ));\n                  }}\n                />\n                <Input\n                  label=\"Handicap:\"\n                  type=\"number\"\n                  value={player.handicap}\n                  onChange={(e) => {\n                    setComputerPlayers(players => players.map((p, i) => \n                      i === index ? { ...p, handicap: e.target.value } : p\n                    ));\n                  }}\n                />\n              </div>\n              \n              <Select\n                label=\"Personality:\"\n                value={player.personality}\n                onChange={(e) => {\n                  setComputerPlayers(players => players.map((p, i) => \n                    i === index ? { ...p, personality: e.target.value } : p\n                  ));\n                }}\n                options={personalities.map(p => ({ value: p.id, label: p.name }))}\n                placeholder=\"Select personality...\"\n              />\n              \n              <Button \n                variant=\"secondary\"\n                size=\"small\"\n                onClick={() => openGhinLookup(`comp${index+1}`)}\n                style={{ marginTop: theme.spacing }}\n              >\n                Lookup GHIN Handicap\n              </Button>\n              \n              {ghinLookupSlot === `comp${index+1}` && (\n                <Card variant=\"info\" style={{ marginTop: theme.spacing }}>\n                  <h4>GHIN Handicap Lookup</h4>\n                  <Input\n                    placeholder=\"First Name (optional)\"\n                    value={ghinLookupFirstName}\n                    onChange={e => setGhinLookupFirstName(e.target.value)}\n                  />\n                  <Input\n                    placeholder=\"Last Name (required)\"\n                    value={ghinLookupLastName}\n                    onChange={e => setGhinLookupLastName(e.target.value)}\n                  />\n                  <div style={{ display: 'flex', gap: theme.spacing, marginTop: theme.spacing }}>\n                    <Button \n                      size=\"small\"\n                      onClick={doGhinLookup} \n                      disabled={ghinLookupLoading}\n                    >\n                      Search\n                    </Button>\n                    <Button \n                      variant=\"error\"\n                      size=\"small\"\n                      onClick={closeGhinLookup}\n                    >\n                      Cancel\n                    </Button>\n                  </div>\n                  \n                  {ghinLookupLoading && <div style={{ color: theme.colors.textSecondary, marginTop: 8 }}>Searching...</div>}\n                  {ghinLookupError && <div style={{ color: theme.colors.error, marginTop: 8 }}>{ghinLookupError}</div>}\n                  \n                  {ghinLookupResults.length > 0 && (\n                    <div style={{ marginTop: theme.spacing }}>\n                      <h5>Results:</h5>\n                      {ghinLookupResults.map((g, idx) => (\n                        <div \n                          key={idx} \n                          style={{ \n                            padding: 8, \n                            border: `1px solid ${theme.colors.border}`, \n                            borderRadius: 6, \n                            marginBottom: 4, \n                            cursor: \"pointer\", \n                            background: theme.colors.paper \n                          }} \n                          onClick={() => selectGhinGolfer(g)}\n                        >\n                          <strong>{g.name}</strong> (H: {g.handicap}) \n                          {g.club && <span style={{ color: theme.colors.textSecondary }}>@ {g.club}</span>}\n                        </div>\n                      ))}\n                    </div>\n                  )}\n                </Card>\n              )}\n              \n              <div style={{ marginTop: theme.spacing }}>\n
