const resolveMockPreset = useCallback(\n    () => getSimulationMock(SIMULATION_MOCK_PRESET),\n    []\n  );\n\n  const pushMockTimelineEvent = (partialEvent) => {\n    setTimelineEvents((previous) => [\n      {\n        id: partialEvent.id || `mock-event-${Date.now()}`,\n        timestamp: partialEvent.timestamp || new Date().toISOString(),\n        ...partialEvent,\n      },\n      ...previous,\n    ]);\n  };\n\n  const hydrateMockSetup = useCallback(() => {\n    if (!isMockSessionEnabled) {\n      return;\n    }\n\n    const preset = resolveMockPreset();\n    if (!preset) {\n      return;\n    }\n\n    const { setup, gameState: presetGameState } = preset;\n\n    if (setup) {\n      setPersonalities(setup.personalities || []);\n      setSuggestedOpponents(setup.opponents || []);\n      setCourses(setup.courses || {});\n\n      if (Array.isArray(setup.opponents) && setup.opponents.length > 0) {\n        setComputerPlayers(\n          setup.opponents.slice(0, 3).map((opponent, index) => ({\n            id: opponent.id || `mock-opponent-${index + 1}`,\n            name: opponent.name,\n            handicap: opponent.handicap,\n            personality: opponent.personality,\n            is_human: false,\n          }))\n        );\n      }\n    }\n\n    if (presetGameState?.players) {\n      const humanPlayerFromPreset = presetGameState.players.find(\n        (player) => player?.is_human || player?.id === \"human\"\n      );\n\n      if (humanPlayerFromPreset) {\n        setHumanPlayer((prev) => ({\n          ...prev,\n          ...humanPlayerFromPreset,\n        }));\n      }\n    }\n  }, [isMockSessionEnabled, resolveMockPreset, setPersonalities, setSuggestedOpponents, setCourses, setComputerPlayers, setHumanPlayer]);\n\n  const runMockSimulation = () => {\n    const preset = resolveMockPreset();\n    if (!preset) {\n      return;\n    }\n\n    setGameState(preset.gameState);\n    startGame(preset.gameState);\n    setShotState(preset.shotState || null);\n    setShotProbabilities(preset.shotProbabilities || null);\n    setHasNextShot(\n      preset.hasNextShot !== undefined ? Boolean(preset.hasNextShot) : true\n    );\n    setInteractionNeeded(preset.interactionNeeded || null);\n\n    clearFeedback();\n    (preset.feedback || []).forEach((entry) => addFeedback(entry));\n\n    setTimelineEvents(preset.timelineEvents || []);\n    setPokerState(preset.pokerState || {});\n    setBettingOptions(preset.bettingOptions || []);\n    setMockStep(0);\n  };\n\n  const handleMockDecision = (decision) => {\n    if (!isMockSessionEnabled) {\n      return;\n    }\n\n    if (decision.offer_double !== undefined) {\n      handleBettingAction(\n        decision.offer_double ? 'offer_double' : 'decline_double',\n        {\n          label: decision.offer_double ? 'Offer Double' : 'Decline Double',\n        }\n      );\n      setInteractionNeeded(null);\n      setPendingDecision({});\n      return;\n    }\n\n    if (decision.accept_double !== undefined) {\n      handleBettingAction(\n        decision.accept_double ? 'accept_double' : 'decline_double',\n        {\n          label: decision.accept_double ? 'Accept Double' : 'Decline Double',\n        }\n      );\n      setInteractionNeeded(null);\n      setPendingDecision({});\n      return;\n    }\n\n    if (decision.accept_partnership !== undefined) {\n      const accepted = Boolean(decision.accept_partnership);\n      pushMockTimelineEvent({\n        type: accepted ? 'partnership' : 'solo',\n        description: accepted\n          ? 'Mock: Partnership accepted. Robots brace for teamwork.'\n          : 'Mock: Partnership declined. Captain must go solo.',\n      });\n      addFeedback(\n        accepted\n          ? '‚úÖ Mock confirmation: partnership locked in.'\n          : '‚ö†Ô∏è Mock decline: prepare for solo play.'\n      );\n\n      if (!accepted) {\n        handleBettingAction('offer_double', { label: 'Forced Solo Double' });\n      }\n\n      setInteractionNeeded(null);\n      setPendingDecision({});\n      return;\n    }\n\n    if (decision.action === 'request_partner') {\n      const partnerId = decision.requested_partner;\n      const partnerName =\n        gameState?.players?.find((player) => player.id === partnerId)?.name || partnerId || 'selected partner';\n\n      pushMockTimelineEvent({\n        type: 'partnership',\n        description: `Mock: You selected ${partnerName} as your partner.`,\n      });\n\n      addFeedback(`ü§ù Mock partner secured: ${partnerName}`);\n\n      const pressurePreset = getSimulationMock('pressureDouble');\n      setInteractionNeeded(pressurePreset.interactionNeeded || null);\n      setShotState(pressurePreset.shotState || shotState);\n      setShotProbabilities(pressurePreset.shotProbabilities || shotProbabilities);\n      setBettingOptions(pressurePreset.bettingOptions || bettingOptions);\n      setPokerState((previous) => ({\n        ...previous,\n        ...pressurePreset.pokerState,\n      }));\n      setMockStep((previous) => previous + 1);\n      setPendingDecision({});\n      return;\n    }\n\n    if (decision.action === 'go_solo') {\n      pushMockTimelineEvent({\n        type: 'solo',\n        description: 'Mock: Captain elects to go solo and press the wager.',\n      });\n      addFeedback('üöÄ Mock solo play engaged. The wager has been doubled.');\n      handleBettingAction('offer_double', { label: 'Mock Solo Double' });\n      setInteractionNeeded(null);\n      setPendingDecision({});\n      return;\n    }\n\n    if (decision.action === 'keep_watching') {\n      pushMockTimelineEvent({\n        type: 'captain',\n        description: 'Mock: Captain keeps observing robot tee shots.',\n      });\n      addFeedback('üëÄ Mock mode: continuing to observe tee shots.');\n      setInteractionNeeded(null);\n      setPendingDecision({});\n      return;\n    }\n\n    pushMockTimelineEvent({\n      type: 'info',\n      description: `Mock decision recorded: ${JSON.stringify(decision)}`,\n    });\n    addFeedback('‚ÑπÔ∏è Mock decision logged. No backend action triggered.');\n    setInteractionNeeded(null);\n    setPendingDecision({});\n  };\n\n  const fetchInitialData = useCallback(async () => {\n    if (isMockSessionEnabled) {\n      return;\n    }\n\n    try {\n      const [personalitiesRes, opponentsRes, coursesRes] = await Promise.all([\n        fetch(`${SIMULATION_API_URL}/simulation/available-personalities`),\n        fetch(`${SIMULATION_API_URL}/simulation/suggested-opponents`),\n        fetch(`${SIMULATION_API_URL}/courses`)\n      ]);\n\n      const personalitiesData = await personalitiesRes.json();\n      const opponentsData = await opponentsRes.json();\n      const coursesData = await coursesRes.json();\n\n      setPersonalities(personalitiesData.personalities || []);\n      setSuggestedOpponents(opponentsData.opponents || []);\n      setCourses(coursesData || {});\n\n      if (opponentsData.opponents && opponentsData.opponents.length >= 3) {\n        setComputerPlayers([\n          { id: \"comp1\", ...opponentsData.opponents[0], is_human: false },\n          { id: \"comp2\", ...opponentsData.opponents[1], is_human: false },\n          { id: \"comp3\", ...opponentsData.opponents[2], is_human: false }\n        ]);\n      }\n    } catch (error) {\n      console.error(\"Error fetching initial data:\", error);\n    }\n  }, [isMockSessionEnabled, setComputerPlayers, setCourses, setPersonalities, setSuggestedOpponents]);\n\n  const fetchTurnBasedState = useCallback(async () => {\n    if (isMockSessionEnabled) {\n      return;\n    }\n\n    try {\n      const response = await fetch(`${SIMULATION_API_URL}/simulation/turn-based-state`);\n      const data = await response.json();\n\n      if (data.success) {\n        setTurnBasedState(data.turn_based_state);\n      }\n    } catch (error) {\n      console.error('Error fetching turn-based state:', error);\n    }\n  }, [isMockSessionEnabled, setTurnBasedState]);\n\n  useEffect(() => {\n    if (isMockSessionEnabled) {\n      hydrateMockSetup();\n      return;\n    }\n\n    fetchInitialData();\n  }, [fetchInitialData, hydrateMockSetup, isMockSessionEnabled]);\n  \n  // Fetch turn-based state when game is active\n  useEffect(() => {\n    if (isGameActive && useTurnBasedMode && !isMockSessionEnabled) {\n      fetchTurnBasedState();\n      const interval = setInterval(fetchTurnBasedState, 2000);\n      return () => clearInterval(interval);\n    }\n    return undefined;\n  }, [fetchTurnBasedState, isGameActive, isMockSessionEnabled, useTurnBasedMode]);\n  const startSimulation = async () => {\n    if (!isMockSessionEnabled && !humanPlayer.name.trim()) {\n      alert(\"Please enter your name\");\n      return;\n    }\n\n    setLoading(true);\n    try {\n      // Reset all local state for new simulation\n      setGameState(null);\n      endGame();  // Use endGame directly instead of setIsGameActive\n      clearFeedback();\n      setShotProbabilities(null);\n      setShotState(null);\n      setHasNextShot(true);\n      setInteractionNeeded(null);\n      setPendingDecision({});\n      setHoleDecisions({\n        action: null,\n        requested_partner: null,\n        offer_double: false,\n        accept_double: false\n      });\n      // GHIN lookup state reset removed - functionality not currently used\n\n      setMockStep(0);\n\n      if (isMockSessionEnabled) {\n        runMockSimulation();\n        setLoading(false);\n        return;\n      }\n\n      const response = await fetch(`${SIMULATION_API_URL}/simulation/setup`, {\n        method: \"POST\",\n        headers: { \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\" },\n        body: JSON.stringify({\n          human_player: humanPlayer,\n          computer_players: computerPlayers,\n          course_name: selectedCourse || null\n        })\n      });\n      \n      const data = await response.json();\n      if (data.status === \"ok\") {\n        // First set the game state\n        setGameState(data.game_state);\n        \n        // Then start the game with the new state\n        startGame(data.game_state);\n        \n        // Set initial feedback\n        clearFeedback();\n        if (data.feedback && Array.isArray(data.feedback)) {\n          data.feedback.forEach((msg) => addFeedback(msg));\n        } else {\n          addFeedback(data.message || \"Simulation started!\");\n        }\n        \n        // Set next shot availability from the response\n        if (data.next_shot_available !== undefined) {\n          setHasNextShot(data.next_shot_available);\n        } else {\n          setHasNextShot(true);  // Default to true after setup\n        }\n        \n        // Don't immediately play next shot - let the user initiate\n        // This prevents race conditions and gives user control\n      } else {\n        alert(\"Error starting simulation: \" + (formatErrorDetail(data.detail) || \"Unknown error\"));\n      }\n    } catch (error) {\n      console.error(\"Error starting simulation:\", error);\n      alert(\"Error starting simulation\");\n    } finally {\n      if (!isMockSessionEnabled) {\n        setLoading(false);\n      }\n    }\n  };\n\n  // Fetch timeline events from backend\n  const fetchTimelineEvents = async () => {\n    if (!isGameActive || isMockSessionEnabled) return;\n    \n    try {\n      setTimelineLoading(true);\n      const response = await fetch(`${SIMULATION_API_URL}/simulation/timeline`);\n      if (response.ok) {\n        const data = await response.json();\n        setTimelineEvents(data.events || []);\n      }\n    } catch (error) {\n      console.error(\"Error fetching timeline:\", error);\n    } finally {\n      setTimelineLoading(false);\n    }\n  };\n\n  // Fetch poker-style betting state\n  const fetchPokerState = async () => {\n    if (!isGameActive || isMockSessionEnabled) return;\n    \n    try {\n      const response = await fetch(`${SIMULATION_API_URL}/simulation/poker-state`);\n      if (response.ok) {\n        const data = await response.json();\n        setPokerState({\n          pot_size: data.pot_size,\n          base_bet: data.base_bet, \n          current_bet: data.current_bet,\n          betting_phase: data.betting_phase,\n          doubled: data.doubled,\n          players_in: data.players_in,\n          wagering_closed: data.wagering_closed\n        });\n        setBettingOptions(data.betting_options || []);\n      }\n    } catch (error) {\n      console.error(\"Error fetching poker state:\", error);\n    }\n  };\n\n  // Handle poker-style betting actions\n  const handleBettingAction = async (action, option) => {\n    if (isMockSessionEnabled) {\n      const label = option?.label || action;\n      const currentWager = gameState?.betting?.current_wager ?? gameState?.base_wager ?? 1;\n      const updatedWager = action === 'offer_double' ? currentWager * 2 : currentWager;\n\n      setGameState((previous) => {\n        if (!previous) {\n          return previous;\n        }\n\n        return {\n          ...previous,\n          betting: {\n            ...(previous.betting || {}),\n            current_wager: updatedWager,\n          },\n        };\n      });\n\n      setPokerState((previous) => ({\n        ...previous,\n        current_wager:\n          action === 'offer_double'\n            ? (previous?.current_wager ?? currentWager) * 2\n            : previous?.current_wager ?? updatedWager,\n        pending_actions: [],\n        last_mock_action: action,\n      }));\n\n      pushMockTimelineEvent({\n        type: action?.includes('double') ? 'double' : 'bet',\n        description: `Mock: ${label}`,\n      });\n\n      addFeedback(`üÉè Mock betting action captured: ${label}`);\n      return;\n    }\n\n    try {\n      setLoading(true);\n\n      const decision = {\n        decision_type: action,\n        player_id: 'human',\n        amount: option.amount || 0,\n        ...option\n      };\n\n      const response = await fetch(`${SIMULATION_API_URL}/simulation/betting-decision`, {\n        method: 'POST',\n        headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },\n        body: JSON.stringify(decision)\n      });\n\n      if (response.ok) {\n        const result = await response.json();\n        if (result.success) {\n          // Update game state if provided\n          if (result.game_state) {\n            setGameState(result.game_state);\n          }\n\n          // Refresh timeline and poker state\n          await Promise.all([fetchTimelineEvents(), fetchPokerState()]);\n        }\n      }\n    } catch (error) {\n      console.error(\"Error handling betting action:\", error);\n    } finally {\n      setLoading(false);\n    }\n  };\n\n  // Auto-refresh timeline and poker state when game is active\n  useEffect(() => {\n    if (isGameActive && !isMockSessionEnabled) {\n      // Initial fetch\n      fetchTimelineEvents();\n      fetchPokerState();\n\n      // Set up polling for real-time updates\n      const interval = setInterval(() => {\n        fetchTimelineEvents();\n        fetchPokerState();\n      }, 3000); // Update every 3 seconds\n\n      return () => clearInterval(interval);\n    }\n    // eslint-disable-next-line react-hooks/exhaustive-deps\n  }, [isGameActive, gameState?.current_hole, gameState?.hole_state?.current_shot_number]); // fetchTimelineEvents and fetchPokerState are stable\n  \n  // Removed unused testNewEndpoints function\n\n  // Add the missing makeDecision function and improve interactive flow\n  const makeDecision = async (decision) => {\n    if (isMockSessionEnabled) {\n      handleMockDecision(decision);\n      return;\n    }\n\n    setLoading(true);\n    try {\n      // Determine which endpoint to use based on decision type\n      let endpoint = '/simulation/play-hole';\n      let payload = { ...decision };\n      \n      // Handle different decision types\n      if (decision.action === 'request_partner' || decision.action === 'go_solo' || decision.action === 'keep_watching') {\n        // Captain decisions during tee shots\n        endpoint = '/simulation/play-hole';\n        payload = {\n          action: decision.action,\n          requested_partner: decision.requested_partner || decision.partner_id\n        };\n      } else if (decision.accept_partnership !== undefined) {\n        // Partnership response\n        endpoint = '/simulation/play-hole';\n        payload = {\n          accept_partnership: decision.accept_partnership\n        };\n      } else if (decision.offer_double !== undefined) {\n        // Doubling decisions\n        endpoint = '/simulation/betting-decision';\n        payload = {\n          action: decision.offer_double ? 'offer_double' : 'decline_double'\n        };\n      } else if (decision.accept_double !== undefined) {\n        // Double response\n        endpoint = '/simulation/betting-decision';\n        payload = {\n          action: decision.accept_double ? 'accept_double' : 'decline_double'\n        };\n      }\n\n      const response = await fetch(`${SIMULATION_API_URL}${endpoint}`, {\n        method: \"POST\",\n        headers: { \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\" },\n        body: JSON.stringify(payload)\n      });\n      \n      if (!response.ok) {\n        const errorText = await response.text();\n        throw new Error(`Backend error: ${response.status} - ${errorText}`);\n      }\n      \n      const data = await response.json();\n      \n      if (data.status === \"ok\") {\n        // Update game state\n        setGameState(data.game_state);\n        \n        // Add feedback messages\n        if (data.feedback && Array.isArray(data.feedback)) {\n          data.feedback.forEach(msg => addFeedback(msg));\n        } else if (data.decision_result?.message) {\n          addFeedback(`üí∞ ${data.decision_result.message}`);\n        }\n        \n        // Handle interaction needed\n        if (data.interaction_needed) {\n          setInteractionNeeded(data.interaction_needed);\n        } else {\n          setInteractionNeeded(null);\n          setPendingDecision({});\n        }\n        \n        // Update shot state if available\n        if (data.next_shot_available !== undefined) {\n          setHasNextShot(data.next_shot_available);\n        }\n        \n        const baseProbabilities =\n          data.probabilities && typeof data.probabilities === \"object\" && !Array.isArray(data.probabilities)\n            ? data.probabilities\n            : null;\n\n        const bettingAnalysis =\n          data.betting_probabilities && typeof data.betting_probabilities === \"object\"\n            ? data.betting_probabilities\n            : null;\n\n        if (baseProbabilities || bettingAnalysis) {\n          const combinedProbabilities = {\n            ...(baseProbabilities || {}),\n            ...(bettingAnalysis ? { betting_analysis: bettingAnalysis } : {}),\n          };\n\n          setShotProbabilities(combinedProbabilities);\n        }\n        \n        // Auto-continue if no interaction needed and shots available\n        if (!data.interaction_needed && data.next_shot_available) {\n          // Small delay to let user see the feedback\n          setTimeout(() => {\n            if (!loading && !interactionNeeded) {\n              playNextShot();\n            }\n          }, 1500);\n        }\n        \n      } else {\n        throw new Error(data.message || 'Unknown error occurred');\n      }\n      \n    } catch (error) {\n      console.error(\"Error making decision:\", error);\n      \n      // Provide user-friendly error messages\n      let errorMessage = \"Error making decision: \";\n      if (error.message.includes(\"Backend error: 500\")) {\n        errorMessage += \"Server error - please try again\";\n      } else if (error.message.includes(\"Backend error: 400\")) {\n        errorMessage += \"Invalid decision - please check your choice\";\n      } else if (error.message.includes(\"fetch\")) {\n        errorMessage += \"Network error - check your connection\";\n      } else {\n        errorMessage += error.message;\n      }\n      \n      // Add error to feedback instead of alert\n      addFeedback(`‚ùå ${errorMessage}`);\n      \n      // Clear interaction needed to prevent stuck state\n      setInteractionNeeded(null);\n    } finally {\n      setLoading(false);\n    }\n  };\n  \n  const playNextShot = async () => {\n    if (loading || interactionNeeded) {\n      if (process.env.NODE_ENV !== 'production') {\n        console.debug(\"Cannot play shot:\", { loading, interactionNeeded });\n      }\n      return;\n    }\n\n    if (isMockSessionEnabled) {\n      const presetName = mockStep % 2 === 0 ? 'pressureDouble' : SIMULATION_MOCK_PRESET;\n      const nextPreset = getSimulationMock(presetName);\n\n      pushMockTimelineEvent({\n        type: 'shot',\n        description:\n          nextPreset.shotState?.recommended_shot ||\n          `Mock shot progression ${mockStep + 1}.`,\n      });\n\n      addFeedback(`üéØ Mock shot advanced (step ${mockStep + 1}).`);\n\n      setGameState((previous) => {\n        if (!previous) {\n          return nextPreset.gameState || previous;\n        }\n\n        const nextHoleState = {\n          ...(previous.hole_state || {}),\n          ...((nextPreset.gameState && nextPreset.gameState.hole_state) || {}),\n          current_shot_number:\n            (previous.hole_state?.current_shot_number || 0) + 1,\n        };\n\n        return {\n          ...previous,\n          ...(nextPreset.gameState || {}),\n          hole_state: nextHoleState,\n        };\n      });\n\n      setShotState(nextPreset.shotState || null);\n      setShotProbabilities(nextPreset.shotProbabilities || null);\n      setInteractionNeeded(nextPreset.interactionNeeded || null);\n      setBettingOptions(nextPreset.bettingOptions || bettingOptions);\n      setPokerState((previous) => ({\n        ...previous,\n        ...nextPreset.pokerState,\n      }));\n      setHasNextShot(\n        nextPreset.hasNextShot !== undefined\n          ? Boolean(nextPreset.hasNextShot)\n          : false\n      );\n      setMockStep((previous) => previous + 1);\n      return;\n    }\n\n    setLoading(true);\n    try {\n      const response = await fetch(`${SIMULATION_API_URL}/simulation/play-next-shot`, {\n        method: \"POST\",\n        headers: { \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\" },\n        body: JSON.stringify(pendingDecision)\n      });\n      \n      if (!response.ok) {\n        const errorText = await response.text();\n        throw new Error(`Backend error: ${response.status} - ${errorText}`);\n      }\n      \n      const data = await response.json();\n      \n      if (data.status === \"ok\") {\n        setGameState(data.game_state);\n        \n        // Add feedback from the shot simulation\n        if (data.feedback && data.feedback.length > 0) {\n          data.feedback.forEach(msg => addFeedback(msg));\n        }\n        \n        // Handle shot result\n        if (data.shot_result) {\n          addFeedback(`üéØ Shot Result: ${JSON.stringify(data.shot_result)}`);\n        }\n        \n        // Handle interaction needed\n        if (data.interaction_needed) {\n          setInteractionNeeded(data.interaction_needed);\n          setPendingDecision({});\n        } else {\n          setInteractionNeeded(null);\n          setPendingDecision({});\n        }\n        \n        // Update next shot availability\n        setHasNextShot(data.next_shot_available);\n        \n        // Refresh timeline and poker state after shot\n        await Promise.all([fetchTimelineEvents(), fetchPokerState()]);\n        \n      } else {\n        throw new Error(data.message || 'Unknown error occurred');\n      }\n      \n    } catch (error) {\n      console.error(\"Error playing next shot:\", error);\n      \n      let errorMessage = \"Error playing shot: \";\n      if (error.message.includes(\"Backend error: 500\")) {\n        errorMessage += \"Server error - please try again\";\n      } else if (error.message.includes(\"fetch\")) {\n        errorMessage += \"Network error - check your connection\";\n      } else {\n        errorMessage += error.message;\n      }\n      \n      addFeedback(`‚ùå ${errorMessage}`);\n    } finally {\n      setLoading(false);\n    }\n  };\n  \n  const resetSimulation = () => {\n    setGameState(null);\n    endGame();  // Use endGame directly instead of setIsGameActive\n    clearFeedback();\n    setHoleDecisions({\n      action: null,\n      requested_partner: null,\n      offer_double: false,\n      accept_double: false\n    });\n    setMockStep(0);\n  };\n  \n  if (!isGameActive) {\n    return (\n      <GameSetup\n        humanPlayer={humanPlayer}\n        setHumanPlayer={setHumanPlayer}\n        computerPlayers={computerPlayers}\n        setComputerPlayers={setComputerPlayers}\n        selectedCourse={selectedCourse}\n        setSelectedCourse={setSelectedCourse}\n        courses={courses}\n        setCourses={setCourses}\n        personalities={personalities}\n        setPersonalities={setPersonalities}\n        suggestedOpponents={suggestedOpponents}\n        setSuggestedOpponents={setSuggestedOpponents}\n        onStartGame={startSimulation}\n      />\n    );\n  }\n\n  // Choose interface based on mode preference\n  if (useTurnBasedMode && turnBasedState) {\n    return (\n      <TurnBasedInterface\n        gameState={{\n          ...gameState,\n          ...(turnBasedState.turn_based_state || turnBasedState),\n          interactionNeeded,\n          hasNextShot,\n          feedback\n        }}\n        onMakeDecision={makeDecision}\n        interactionNeeded={interactionNeeded}\n        feedback={feedback}\n        shotState={shotState}\n        onNextShot={playNextShot}\n        hasNextShot={hasNextShot}\n      />\n    );\n  }\n  \n  // Use Enhanced Simulation Layout with Timeline and Poker Betting\n  const useEnhancedLayout = true; // TODO: Make this a user preference\n\n  if (useEnhancedLayout) {\n    return (\n      <EnhancedSimulationLayout\n        gameState={gameState}\n        shotState={shotState}\n        probabilities={shotProbabilities}\n        onDecision={makeDecision}\n        onPlayNextShot={playNextShot}\n        timelineEvents={timelineEvents}\n        timelineLoading={timelineLoading}\n        pokerState={pokerState}\n        bettingOptions={bettingOptions}\n        onBettingAction={handleBettingAction}\n        currentPlayer=\"human\"\n        interactionNeeded={interactionNeeded}\n        hasNextShot={hasNextShot}\n        feedback={feedback}\n      />\n    );\n  }\n\n  return (\n    <GamePlay\n      gameState={gameState}\n      onEndSimulation={resetSimulation}\n Please login first.');}try{const golferInfo=await this.client.getGolfer(ghinId);return{ghinId:golferInfo.ghinId||ghinId,name:golferInfo.name,handicapIndex:golferInfo.handicapIndex,club:golferInfo.club,lastUpdated:golferInfo.lastUpdated,recentScores:golferInfo.recentScores||[]};}catch(error){console.error(`Failed to get golfer info for GHIN ID ${ghinId}:`,error);throw error;}}/**\n   * Get recent scores for a golfer\n   * @param {string} ghinId - GHIN ID of the golfer\n   * @param {number} limit - Number of recent scores to fetch (default: 20)\n   */async getRecentScores(ghinId){let limit=arguments.length>1&&arguments[1]!==undefined?arguments[1]:20;if(!this.isInitialized()){throw new Error('GHIN service not initialized. Please login first.');}try{const scores=await this.client.getScores(ghinId,limit);return scores.map(score=>({date:score.date,course:score.course,tees:score.tees,score:score.score,courseRating:score.courseRating,slopeRating:score.slopeRating,differential:score.differential,posted:score.posted}));}catch(error){console.error(`Failed to get recent scores for GHIN ID ${ghinId}:`,error);throw error;}}/**\n   * Get handicap index for a golfer\n   * @param {string} ghinId - GHIN ID of the golfer\n   */async getHandicapIndex(ghinId){if(!this.isInitialized()){throw new Error('GHIN service not initialized. Please login first.');}try{const golferInfo=await this.getGolferInfo(ghinId);return{ghinId:ghinId,handicapIndex:golferInfo.handicapIndex,lastUpdated:golferInfo.lastUpdated};}catch(error){console.error(`Failed to get handicap index for GHIN ID ${ghinId}:`,error);throw error;}}/**\n   * Get multiple golfers' information in batch\n   * @param {string[]} ghinIds - Array of GHIN IDs\n   */async getBatchGolferInfo(ghinIds){if(!this.isInitialized()){throw new Error('GHIN service not initialized. Please login first.');}const results=[];const errors=[];for(const ghinId of ghinIds){try{const golferInfo=await this.getGolferInfo(ghinId);results.push(golferInfo);}catch(error){errors.push({ghinId,error:error.message});console.warn(`Failed to fetch data for GHIN ID ${ghinId}:`,error.message);}}return{success:results,errors:errors,totalRequested:ghinIds.length,totalSuccess:results.length,totalErrors:errors.length};}/**\n   * Search for golfers by name (if supported by the API)\n   * @param {string} name - Name to search for\n   */async searchGolfers(name){if(!this.isInitialized()){throw new Error('GHIN service not initialized. Please login first.');}try{// Note: This method might not be available in all versions of the GHIN API\nconst results=await this.client.searchGolfers(name);return results.map(golfer=>({ghinId:golfer.ghinId,name:golfer.name,club:golfer.club,handicapIndex:golfer.handicapIndex}));}catch(error){console.error(`Failed to search for golfers named ${name}:`,error);throw error;}}/**\n   * Post a score for a golfer (if supported)\n   * @param {string} ghinId - GHIN ID of the golfer\n   * @param {Object} scoreData - Score information\n   */async postScore(ghinId,scoreData){if(!this.isInitialized()){throw new Error('GHIN service not initialized. Please login first.');}try{const result=await this.client.postScore(ghinId,{date:scoreData.date,course:scoreData.course,tees:scoreData.tees,score:scoreData.score,courseRating:scoreData.courseRating,slopeRating:scoreData.slopeRating});return result;}catch(error){console.error(`Failed to post score for GHIN ID ${ghinId}:`,error);throw error;}}/**\n   * Logout and cleanup\n   */async logout(){if(this.client){try{await this.client.logout();}catch(error){console.warn('Error during logout:',error);}this.client=null;this.initialized=false;}}}// Create singleton instance\nconst ghinService=new GHINService();// Helper function to initialize with environment variables or stored credentials\nexport const initializeGHIN=async(username,password)=>{if(!username||!password){// Try to get from environment variables\nusername=process.env.REACT_APP_GHIN_USERNAME;password=process.env.REACT_APP_GHIN_PASSWORD;}if(!username||!password){console.warn('GHIN credentials not provided. GHIN username\n   * @param {string} password - GHIN password\n   */\n  async initialize(username, password) {\n    try {\n      this.client = new GhinClient(username, password);\n      await this.client.login();\n      this.initialized = true;\n      if (process.env.NODE_ENV !== 'production') {\n        console.debug('GHIN client initialized successfully');\n      }\n      return true;\n    } catch (error) {\n      console.error('Failed to initialize GHIN client:', error);\n      this.initialized = false;\n      return false;\n    }\n  }\n\n  /**\n   * Check if GHIN service is initialized and authenticated\n   */\n  isInitialized() {\n    return this.initialized && this.client;\n  }\n\n  /**\n   * Get golfer information by GHIN ID\n   * @param {string} ghinId - GHIN ID of the golfer\n   */\n  async getGolferInfo(ghinId) {\n    if (!this.isInitialized()) {\n      throw new Error('GHIN service not initialized. Please login first.');\n    }\n\n    try {\n      const golferInfo = await this.client.getGolfer(ghinId);\n      return {\n        ghinId: golferInfo.ghinId || ghinId,\n        name: golferInfo.name,\n        handicapIndex: golferInfo.handicapIndex,\n        club: golferInfo.club,\n        lastUpdated: golferInfo.lastUpdated,\n        recentScores: golferInfo.recentScores || []\n      };\n    } catch (error) {\n      console.error(`Failed to get golfer info for GHIN ID ${ghinId}:`, error);\n      throw error;\n    }\n  }\n\n  /**\n   * Get recent scores for a golfer\n   * @param {string} ghinId - GHIN ID of the golfer\n   * @param {number} limit - Number of recent scores to fetch (default: 20)\n   */\n  async getRecentScores(ghinId, limit = 20) {\n    if (!this.isInitialized()) {\n      throw new Error('GHIN service not initialized. Please login first.');\n    }\n\n    try {\n      const scores = await this.client.getScores(ghinId, limit);\n      return scores.map(score => ({\n        date: score.date,\n        course: score.course,\n        tees: score.tees,\n        score: score.score,\n        courseRating: score.courseRating,\n        slopeRating: score.slopeRating,\n        differential: score.differential,\n        posted: score.posted\n      }));\n    } catch (error) {\n      console.error(`Failed to get recent scores for GHIN ID ${ghinId}:`, error);\n      throw error;\n    }\n  }\n\n  /**\n   * Get handicap index for a golfer\n   * @param {string} ghinId - GHIN ID of the golfer\n   */\n  async getHandicapIndex(ghinId) {\n    if (!this.isInitialized()) {\n      throw new Error('GHIN service not initialized. Please login first.');\n    }\n\n    try {\n      const golferInfo = await this.getGolferInfo(ghinId);\n      return {\n        ghinId: ghinId,\n        handicapIndex: golferInfo.handicapIndex,\n        lastUpdated: golferInfo.lastUpdated\n      };\n    } catch (error) {\n      console.error(`Failed to get handicap index for GHIN ID ${ghinId}:`, error);\n      throw error;\n    }\n  }\n\n  /**\n   * Get multiple golfers' information in batch\n   * @param {string[]} ghinIds - Array of GHIN IDs\n   */\n  async getBatchGolferInfo(ghinIds) {\n    if (!this.isInitialized()) {\n      throw new Error('GHIN service not initialized. Please login first.');\n    }\n\n    const results = [];\n    const errors = [];\n\n    for (const ghinId of ghinIds) {\n      try {\n        const golferInfo = await this.getGolferInfo(ghinId);\n        results.push(golferInfo);\n      } catch (error) {\n        errors.push({ ghinId, error: error.message });\n        console.warn(`Failed to fetch data for GHIN ID ${ghinId}:`, error.message);\n      }\n    }\n\n    return {\n      success: results,\n      errors: errors,\n      totalRequested: ghinIds.length,\n      totalSuccess: results.length,\n      totalErrors: errors.length\n    };\n  }\n\n  /**\n   * Search for golfers by name (if supported by the API)\n   * @param {string} name - Name to search for\n   */\n  async searchGolfers(name) {\n    if (!this.isInitialized()) {\n      throw new Error('GHIN service not initialized. Please login first.');\n    }\n\n    try {\n      // Note: This method might not be available in all versions of the GHIN API\n      const results = await this.client.searchGolfers(name);\n      return results.map(golfer => ({\n        ghinId: golfer.ghinId,\n        name: golfer.name,\n        club: golfer.club,\n        handicapIndex: golfer.handicapIndex\n      }));\n    } catch (error) {\n      console.error(`Failed to search for golfers named ${name}:`, error);\n      throw error;\n    }\n  }\n\n  /**\n   * Post a score for a golfer (if supported)\n   * @param {string} ghinId - GHIN ID of the golfer\n   * @param {Object} scoreData - Score information\n   */\n  async postScore(ghinId, scoreData) {\n    if (!this.isInitialized()) {\n      throw new Error('GHIN service not initialized. Please login first.');\n    }\n\n    try {\n      const result = await this.client.postScore(ghinId, {\n        date: scoreData.date,\n        course: scoreData.course,\n        tees: scoreData.tees,\n        score: scoreData.score,\n        courseRating: scoreData.courseRating,\n        slopeRating: scoreData.slopeRating\n      });\n      return result;\n    } catch (error) {\n      console.error(`Failed to post score for GHIN ID ${ghinId}:`, error);\n      throw error;\n    }\n  }\n\n  /**\n   * Logout and cleanup\n   */\n  async logout() {\n    if (this.client) {\n      try {\n        await this.client.logout();\n      } catch (error) {\n        console.warn('Error during logout:', error);\n      }\n      this.client = null;\n      this.initialized = false;\n    }\n  }\n}\n\n// Create singleton instance\nconst ghinService = new GHINService();\n\n// Helper function to initialize with environment variables or stored credentials\nexport const initializeGHIN = async (username, password) => {\n  if (!username || !password) {\n    // Try to get from environment variables\n    username = process.env.REACT_APP_GHIN_USERNAME;\n    password = process.env.REACT_APP_GHIN_PASSWORD;\n  }\n\n  if (!username || !password) {\n    console.warn('GHIN credentials not provided. GHIN integration will be disabled.');\n    return false;\n  }\n\n  return await ghinService.initialize(username, password);\n};\n\nexport default ghinService;\n"],"mappings":"AAAA,OAASA,UAAU,KAAQ,MAAM,CAEjC,KAAM,CAAAC,WAAY,CAChBC,WAAWA,CAAA,CAAG,CACZ,IAAI,CAACC,MAAM,CAAG,IAAI,CAClB,IAAI,CAACC,WAAW,CAAG,KAAK,CAC1B,CAEA;AACF;AACA;AACA;AACA,KACE,KAAM,CAAAC,UAAUA,CAACC,QAAQ,CAAEC,QAAQ,CAAE,CACnC,GAAI,CACF,IAAI,CAACJ,MAAM,CAAG,GAAI,CAAAH,UAAU,CAACM,QAAQ,CAAEC,QAAQ,CAAC,CAChD,KAAM,KAAI,CAACJ,MAAM,CAACK,KAAK,CAAC,CAAC,CACzB,IAAI,CAACJ,WAAW,CAAG,IAAI,CACvB,GAAIK,OAAO,CAACC,GAAG,CAACC,QAAQ,GAAK,YAAY,CAAE,CACzCC,OAAO,CAACC,KAAK,CAAC,sCAAsC,CAAC,CACvD,CACA,MAAO,KAAI,CACb,CAAE,MAAOC,KAAK,CAAE,CACdF,OAAO,CAACE,KAAK,CAAC,mCAAmC,CAAEA,KAAK,CAAC,CACzD,IAAI,CAACV,WAAW,CAAG,KAAK,CACxB,MAAO,MAAK,CACd,CACF,CAEA;AACF;AACA,KACEW,aAAaA,CAAA,CAAG,CACd,MAAO,KAAI,CAACX,WAAW,EAAI,IAAI,CAACD,MAAM,CACxC,CAEA;AACF;AACA;AACA,KACE,KAAM,CAAAa,aAAaA,CAACC,MAAM,CAAE,CAC1B,GAAI,CAAC,IAAI,CAACF,aAAa,CAAC,CAAC,CAAE,CACzB,KAAM,IAAI,CAAAG,KAAK,CAAC,mDAAmD,CAAC,CACtE,CAEA,GAAI,CACF,KAAM,CAAAC,UAAU,CAAG,KAAM,KAAI,CAAChB,MAAM,CAACiB,SAAS,CAACH,MAAM,CAAC,CACtD,MAAO,CACLA,MAAM,CAAEE,UAAU,CAACF,MAAM,EAAIA,MAAM,CACnCI,IAAI,CAAEF,UAAU,CAACE,IAAI,CACrBC,aAAa,CAAEH,UAAU,CAACG,aAAa,CACvCC,IAAI,CAAEJ,UAAU,CAACI,IAAI,CACrBC,WAAW,CAAEL,UAAU,CAACK,WAAW,CACnCC,YAAY,CAAEN,UAAU,CAACM,YAAY,EAAI,EAC3C,CAAC,CACH,CAAE,MAAOX,KAAK,CAAE,CACdF,OAAO,CAACE,KAAK,CAAC,yCAAyCG,MAAM,GAAG,CAAEH,KAAK,CAAC,CACxE,KAAM,CAAAA,KAAK,CACb,CACF,CAEA;AACF;AACA;AACA;AACA,KACE,KAAM,CAAAY,eAAeA,CAACT,MAAM,CAAc,IAAZ,CAAAU,KAAK,CAAAC,SAAA,CAAAC,MAAA,IAAAD,SAAA,MAAAE,SAAA,CAAAF,SAAA,IAAG,EAAE,CACtC,GAAI,CAAC,IAAI,CAACb,aAAa,CAAC,CAAC,CAAE,CACzB,KAAM,IAAI,CAAAG,KAAK,CAAC,mDAAmD,CAAC,CACtE,CAEA,GAAI,CACF,KAAM,CAAAa,MAAM,CAAG,KAAM,KAAI,CAAC5B,MAAM,CAAC6B,SAAS,CAACf,MAAM,CAAEU,KAAK,CAAC,CACzD,MAAO,CAAAI,MAAM,CAACE,GAAG,CAACC,KAAK,GAAK,CAC1BC,IAAI,CAAED,KAAK,CAACC,IAAI,CAChBC,MAAM,CAAEF,KAAK,CAACE,MAAM,CACpBC,IAAI,CAAEH,KAAK,CAACG,IAAI,CAChBH,KAAK,CAAEA,KAAK,CAACA,KAAK,CAClBI,YAAY,CAAEJ,KAAK,CAACI,YAAY,CAChCC,WAAW,CAAEL,KAAK,CAACK,WAAW,CAC9BC,YAAY,CAAEN,KAAK,CAACM,YAAY,CAChCC,MAAM,CAAEP,KAAK,CAACO,MAC
